title: string bean casserole
directions: Combine string beans and mushroom soup; mix thoroughly.
Place in covered dish, approximately 4-inches deep.
Spread cheese and onion evenly over the top.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
May substitute crushed potato chips for toasted onions.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cover cookie sheet with foil.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Slowly add sugar.
Add salt, vanilla and chocolate chips.
Fold together.
Drop on cookie sheet.
Place in preheated oven.
Count to 10.
Turn off oven and leave cookies overnight.
Forget them!

title: christmas refrigerator cookies
directions: Sift flour and soda 3 times.
Mix sugar, eggs and butter.
Mix well.
Make in rolls and refrigerate.
Slice and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Very good.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour before measuring.
After measuring, sift plain flour and self-rising flour together three times.
Add flour and milk, alternating, to mixture of Crisco, eggs and sugar.
Add flavoring of choice (vanilla, butter, lemon or almond).

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cut cabbage in half; put 1/2 in
boiling water and boil until leaves can be separated. Let cool.

Boil rice; add to hamburger, sausage and egg and mix well. Take a small amount of the hamburger and sausage mixture and put it in the center of 1 cabbage leaf. Roll leaf up and tuck ends inward. Proceed until all leaves are used. Put rolled leaves into a 5-qt. pot; pour tomato juice and sauerkraut over rolls. Chop other half of cabbage finely and add to pot. Cook for 1 hour.

title: shrimp pizza
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients until smooth.
Spread on bottom of plate.
Sprinkle shrimp on mixture; sprinkle on top of shrimp with cocktail sauce as needed.
Place on top the cheese, onions, pepper and tomatoes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli with salt until tender and drain.
Mix with mayonnaise, soup and cheese.
Pour in baking dish and top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° until crumbs are brown.

title: ginger ale sherbet
directions: In a saucepan, heat the water and one cup of the sugar to the boiling point and cook until the syrup reaches the soft ball stage (234 to 238°).
Beat the egg whites until stiff.
Continue beating while gradually adding 1/2 cup of the sugar.

Slowly pour the hot syrup into the egg whites, beating constantly until mixture has cooled, then gradually beat in the ginger ale and fruit juices. Place in the freezer until partially frozen, then remove and whip quickly.
Pour into freezing trays, cover and return to the freezer.
The texture should resemble that of an Italian ice.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage together.
Drain well.
Add rest of ingredients. Cook on medium-low until cheese melts.
Stir to keep from sticking.
Spread on rye bread. Freeze.
Heat as needed.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Mix together.
Cook in oven for 4 to 5 hours at 350°.
Serve over noodles.
Can add pint of sour cream.
Easy and very good!

title: georgia cracker salad
directions: In a medium size bowl, coarsely crush the crackers with your hands- you should have big cracker pieces.
Add the remaining ingredients, mix well, and serve immediately.
Season to taste, with salt and pepper.

title: congo squares
directions: Pour brown sugar in bowl.
Pour melted butter over and mix. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add nuts and chocolate chips to flour to coat, then add to sugar/egg mixture.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased 9 x 12-inch pan and bake at 350° about 35 to 40 minutes.
These will collapse in middle of pan, so don't think you have done something wrong.

title: forget-me-not cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add vanilla, salt and sugar gradually.
Mix in chocolate chips and nuts.
Line 2 cookie sheets with foil, drop teaspoonfuls on sheets. When you put cookies in to bake, turn oven off and leave cookies 8 hours.
Do not open oven during the 8 hours.

title: green bean caesar
directions: Toss first 6 ingredients and place in casserole.
Stir remaining ingredients together and sprinkle over beans.
Bake, uncovered, for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: butterscotch bar cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and the shortening; add vanilla and eggs slowly.
Add the remaining ingredients and mix all together.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes in a 17 x 11 x 1-inch pan.

title: feta cheese dip
directions: In a bowl, blend ingredients with a fork and chill.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: my best gingerbread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Mix until fluffy; sift dry ingredients.
Add alternately with hot water and molasses which have been mixed together.
Bake in 325° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: saucy summer fruit
directions: Combine ingredients.
Chill and serve over fresh fruit salad. Makes 1 cup.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Combine salad dressing mix, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Combine green pepper, onion and tomatoes.
Layer cornbread, pinto beans, vegetables, corn, dressing, cheese and bacon, making 2 layers.

title: pork chops with rice
directions: Mix rice, onion soup and beef consomme.
Brown pork chops and place on top of rice mixture in casserole dish.
Cover; bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill overnight and serve.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Combine first five ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in whipped topping.
Pour in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and freeze.

title: homemade butter
directions: Mix well.
Makes 1 large butter tub.

title: potato wedges
directions: Wash potatoes, leave skin on, and cut in wedges.
Mix flour, salt, chili powder, cheese, onion salt, and pepper and put in a bag and shake.
Add potato wedges a few at a time and shake to coat with flour mixture.
Melt margarine in oblong pan.
Place wedges in pan and bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken oriental
directions: Blend all together.
Use half can of noodles in dish and half on top.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal raisin chews
directions: Mix together and drop on greased cookie sheets and bake at 300° for 18 to 22 minutes.

title: freezer ice cream
directions: In electric mixer, beat eggs.
Add salt and sugar.
Beat well. Add vanilla, then evaporated milk, slowly.
Beat continuously; pour in freezer can with homogenized milk.

title: orange rice salad
directions: Combine rice, onion, walnuts, raisins and carrots in large bowl.
Whisk together the orange juice, mayonnaise and salt.
Stir dressing into rice mixture.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: brown rice
directions: Combine all the ingredients and bake at 300° for 1 hour.
I double recipe and bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
In hot oil, brown on all sides.
Push to one side of pan and cook onions, mushrooms and garlic.
Mix tomato paste with remaining ingredients; pour over chicken.
Stir well.
Cover pan and simmer very gently until tender, 30 minutes.
Uncover and simmer until sauce is thick. Serves 4.

title: thelma's hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except eggs.
Put half mixture in casserole dish; slice eggs over the top, then put remaining mixture over the eggs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Top with crushed Rice Krispies.

title: hominy soup
directions: Brown sausage and drain well.
Mix all ingredients in heavy sauce pan.	Heat over medium-high heat until cheese is melted and soup is heated through.
Serve with tortilla chips.
A can of cream soup can be added to make the meal go further.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix cream cheese and Eagle Brand milk.
Add nuts and Cool Whip and mix.
Add can of cherry pie filling and chill.

title: t. c.'s choc-chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar. Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix all remaining ingredients.
Make into golf ball size or your own preference and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 6 minutes.

title: carolina apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs together.
Sift flour, soda, salt and spices together; add to egg mixture.
Mix thoroughly.
Next, add vanilla, apples and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube cake pan and bake at 350° for approximately
1 hour.
Remove cake from pan.
Cool and top with glaze.

title: apricot dream cake
directions: Thicken apricot nectar with sugar and flour; let cool.
Tear angel food cake into bite size pieces and place in oblong dish. Pour nectar mixture over cake.
Spread with prepared Dream Whip. Sprinkle nuts over top.
Refrigerate.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Mix pineapple, sour cream, nuts and cherries.
Add to jello.
Pour into a mold or 8-inch square oiled pan.
Chill 2 hours or until set.
Serve with a dollop of whipped cream.

title: tomatoes stuffed with shrimp
directions: Cut large shrimp in half.
Wash tomatoes.
Remove stem ends and centers; sprinkle with salt.
Combine rice, cheese, egg, seasonings and shrimp.
Place in tomatoes.
Combine butter and crumbs; sprinkle over top of tomatoes.
Place in a well-greased baking dish.
Bake in a moderate oven, 350°, for 20 to 25 minutes or until tomatoes are tender and crumbs browned.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Saute onion and broccoli in melted butter.
Combine cornbread mix, cottage cheese and eggs.
Mix well.
Stir in sauteed vegetables.
Pour into 8 x 11 1/2 x 2-inch greased pan.
Bake about 40 minutes at 350°.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Cook egg
noodles until done.
Spoon into a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Spread cottage cheese over noodles, then ground beef which has
been	lightly browned in a little fat.
Place 1/2 of the cheese strips over meat and half of spaghetti sauce over
cheese. Follow with remaining cheese and sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done. Serves 6.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Press rolls out on a pizza pan (spray with nonstick spray).
Spread sausage on dough.
Sprinkle cheese over sausage.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until nicely browned.

title: heavenly chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a roasting pan.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over chicken.
Marinate for several hours or overnight, turning once.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours, until nicely browned.
Baste occasionally.
Serve with rice.
Freezes well.
Yummy!

title: favorite deviled eggs
directions: In a bowl mix together the eggs, onion, bacon, salt, pepper, mustard and mayonnaise.
Mix until creamy.
Form the mixture into 1-inch balls and roll each in the Cheddar cheese.
Cover the balls and refrigerate until served.
Yields 25 appetizers.

title: fat-free cheesecake
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat egg substitute about 2 minutes.
Add sugar, cornstarch and vanilla.
Set aside.
In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually add egg mixture, stirring well to combine.
Fold in sour cream.
Pour into sprayed glass pie plate or casserole or 10-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Turn oven off and open door a crack and let cook for 1 hour longer.
Let cool at room temperature for 1 hour, then refrigerate for 6 hours.
(If using spring-form pan, remove mold after 3 to 4 hours.)

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Brown meat, onion and pepper in a large skillet.
Add seasoning to taste.
Add corn, beans and tomato sauce.
Cook until flavors are blended.
Grease a large casserole.
Line bottom of casserole with 1/2 of the potatoes.
Add meat mixture and cover with remaining potatoes.
Dot with butter and bake in oven for 45 minutes at 350°.
A good way to use leftover potatoes.

title: turkey corn chowder
directions: Saute onion slowly in butter until tender, but not brown.
Add potatoes, celery, water, salt and bouillon cube.
Cover and cook until potatoes and celery are tender, about 15 minutes.
Add milk, turkey and thyme.
Heat just before serving.
Stir in parsley. Makes 10 cups chowder, 8 to 10 servings.

title: low-fat corn casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet (rinse with hot water to remove fat).
Cook macaroni and drain.
Add meat and corn; mix well.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add fat-free cheese, if desired.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese.
Add sugar and mix.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and mix well.
Bake in tube pan for 90 minutes at 350°.

title: party mix
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large pan or roaster. Bake in very slow oven at 250° for 2 hours.
Stir and turn mixture every 15 minutes. Be careful not to crush cereals.
Makes 8 quarts.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Mix together and place in ovenproof dish.
Bake at 400° for about 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with Doritos or crackers.
Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: pinwheels
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and dressing mix in a bowl. Using 2 slices of meat, spread on mixture.
Place either green stalk of onion or pickle spear at edge of covered meat.
Roll. Chill until firm and slice.
Serve with snack crackers.
Store in covered dish in refrigerator.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain peach syrup into saucepan. Add sugar, vinegar and spices. Bring to a boil. Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes. Pour over peaches and let stand 24 hours in the refrigerator. Could serve on a lettuce leaf and fill centers with a spoonful of currant jelly.

title: sweet potato bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Place pineapple and sweet potatoes in a 10 x 6 inch baking dish; dot with marmalade.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows. Broil until lightly browned.
Makes 6 servings.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine first nine ingredients.
Top with remaining four. Topping will be granular.
Bake at 350° in greased pan 45 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in casserole dish.
Prepare topping.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed, except put the cinnamon and applesauce in batter also.
Mix well, then bake in two 9-inch layers.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Chop broccoli, celery and onions coarsely and simmer in large pot with water uncovered for 10 minutes.
Broccoli should be bright green.
Remove from heat.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and stir over low heat.
Add milk gradually, stirring until smooth.
Simmer 2 to 3 minutes, continuing to stir.
Remove from heat.
Process vegetables and water in blender or food processor in 2 to 3 cup batches until finely chopped, but not quite pureed. Stir into cream sauce.
Heat.
Serve with chopped onions and dollop of yogurt if desired.

title: chicken baked pork chops
directions: Brown chops.
Grease casserole dish.
Mix ingredients.
Lay chops down in rice mixture.
Cover.
Bake at 350°
for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Remove chicken from pot.
Cook noodles in broth until tender.
Bone chicken and cut in small pieces.
Mix chicken, noodles, soups and sour cream.
Pour into large casserole or 2 small ones.
Mix melted butter with stuffing mix.
Sprinkle on top.
Cook at 350° until top is brown and bubbly.

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and set aside.
Mix buttermilk and soda and set aside.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and mix well.
Add pineapple and preserves and mix, then add all dry ingredients and buttermilk alternately.
Hold in reserve 1/4 cup flour to dredge raisins and nuts.
Fold in raisins and nuts.
Reserve 1 1/2 cups cake batter for frosting.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray 3 (9-inch) cake pans with Pam. Pour batter in pans.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli perfect
directions: Cook broccoli 3 minutes; drain well.
Mix beaten egg, onion, mayonnaise, cheese and soup.
Add to cooked broccoli.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Spread with bread crumbs.
Drizzle with butter and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together into a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cotton pickin' cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
I use 3 round cake pans, greased and floured.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes in a 350° oven.
The time will depend on your oven and the number of pans used.
Check the cake often.
Let cake cool completely before frosting.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add bran cereal soaked in buttermilk.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture.
Add bran cereal soaked in boiling water.
Pour in raisins.

title: chinese chewies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, pour in pan.
Bake in 375° oven for 45 minutes.

title: quick n' easy chili
directions: Brown ground beef in heavy saucepan. Add onion and garlic. Cook until tender.
Add kidney beans, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Simmer for 20 minutes. Stir occasionally. Serve.

title: famous chocolate refrigerator roll
directions: Whip cream with vanilla and sugar, or use Cool Whip

title: chocolate almond cookies
directions: Mix soda and flour.
Set aside.
In food processor, add chocolates, sugar and cocoa.
Process until fine (sandy).
Add butter, egg and extracts.
Mix 1 minute.
Add flour and mix; do not overprocess!
Divide into 4 portions.
Wrap in plastic (cylinder shape works best).
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: banana cranberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and cranberries.
Add bananas, sugar, egg, vanilla and oil, mixing thoroughly.
Bake 35 minutes in greased 8-inch square pan.

title: orange-pineapple cake
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and mandarin oranges in large bowl; mix until well blended.
Pour into 3 prepared cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Pour reserved juice over warm cake layers.
Cool cake.
Combine pineapple, whipped topping and pudding mix in bowl; mix until well blended. Spread between layers and over top of cooled cake.
Store in refrigerator.

title: ham and swiss cheese sandwiches(serves 12)
directions: Mix butter, mustard, onion, poppy seed and Accent or seasoning salt together.
Spread mixture on buns.
Add slice of ham and slice of cheese.
Wrap in tin foil and heat in oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana sour cream coffeecake
directions: Combine pecans, 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon; set aside. Combine oleo and 1 cup sugar; cream to light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, bananas and vanilla; stir in sour cream.
Combine remaining dry ingredients; add to creamed mixture and stir just enough to mix.
Sprinkle 1/2 of reserved cinnamon mixture into bottom of well greased Bundt pan; spoon in 1/2 of batter.
Sprinkle rest of cinnamon mix and add rest of batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until done.
Cool 5 minutes on wire rack before turning out.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix all of the above and chill.

title: chocolate-oat chip cookies
directions: Beat butter and sugars until creamy.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Mix well. Stir in oats, chocolate morsels and nuts.
Drop by rounded measuring tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 9 to 10 minutes for a chewy cookie or 12 to 13 minutes for a crisp cookie.

title: candy
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Roll in balls and lay on wax paper, then roll in coconut and put in the refrigerator for 2 hours.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar, Pet milk and margarine until forms a soft ball; test in cold water.
Remove from heat.
Add Fluff or Creme and semi-sweet chips.
Stir until blended.
Add walnuts and vanilla. Pour into a large buttered platter.
Cool and cut into pieces.

title: plum muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients with spoon.
Bake in greased muffin tins at 325° for 12 to 15 minutes.
(Use miniature muffin tins to make bite-size muffins.)

title: apple surprise
directions: Core and slice apples.
Mix cinnamon and sugar together.
Dip apples in sugar and cinnamon mixture.

title: toffee nut bars
directions: Mix shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Stir in flour.
Press and flatten in ungreased oblong 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Let cool slightly, then spread with Nut Coconut Topping.

title: fruit cocktail pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes, dice small, rinse and bring to a boil.
Add salt.
Potatoes are done when fork goes through with ease. Drain the water; let potatoes cool.
Mix in diced onion, celery, eggs, relish, 2 heaping spoons of mayonnaise,
a little mustard and pepper.
May use paprika for color.
Serve chilled.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream oleo, oil, granulated sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add 2 cups of flour with salt, soda and cream of tartar.
Cream.
Add rest of flour.
Mix dough and leave in refrigerator overnight or until cool.
Roll into a ball in sugar; press down with fork.
Or drop by teaspoon and sprinkle sugar on top.
Bake at 350°.
May ice.

title: old fashion coconut pie
directions: Bake in prebaked pie shell (cook until light brown) for 40 minutes or until brownish on top.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Melt butter.
Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour filling into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cool before cutting.

title: gumdrop cake
directions: Wash raisins and dry in warm oven. Cream shortening and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add applesauce and stir to blend.

title: sauteed spinach with garlic
directions: Cook spinach in boiling water, according to directions, reducing cooking time by 2 or 3 minutes.
Rinse with cold water and drain well.
Press between toweling to remove excess moisture. Melt butter in large skillet over medium-low heat.
Add garlic. Cook and stir in the butter about 2 minutes.
Remove garlic and discard.
Add spinach to butter in skillet and cook over medium-high heat, tossing gently until heated through and flavored with the garlic butter.
Season to taste with salt and fresh ground pepper.
Serves 4.

title: martha's good fudge
directions: Put in large bowl, chocolate chips and butter.
Mix and heat to bubbly, sugar, milk, cream of tartar and
salt.
Mix all together and stir until smooth and then add vanilla and nuts. Place in refrigerator 2 hours.

title: baked zucchini casserole
directions: Combine butter and stuffing mix.
Mix 1/2 with other ingredients and put in baking dish, 9 x 12-inch.
Add the rest of the stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Bake cake as directed.
Poke holes into cake, while still hot, with bottom of the handle of a wooden spoon.
Pour condensed milk and chocolate syrup over the warm cake.
Cool.
Frost with a mixture of Cool Whip and Heath bits.

title: chicken marinade
directions: Mix together and bring to a boil.
Clean chicken.
Spread with lemon juice and let marinate while fire gets ready.
Season with garlic salt, seasoned salt, salt and pepper.
Place inside (boney side) down and let it brown.
Move over and cook over indirect heat until done.
Keep basting!

title: sugar-free creamy fruit sauce
directions: Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: rhubarb cherry pie
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 5 ingredients.
Let stand for 15 minutes.
Pour into one of the unbaked pie shell.
Us other pie shell to make a lattice top.
Bake at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes or until the crust is golden and filling is bubbling.

title: cheese straws
directions: Combine flour, cheese and pepper.
Mix until coarse like meal. Add butter and salt.
Mix well.
Run through cookie presser. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: golden glow salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; add orange juice.
Combine remaining ingredients and add to jello mixture.
Put in refrigerator to congeal.
No need to partially congeal before adding fruit and cheese.
This is a quick and easy salad to prepare.

title: a winter soup
directions: Combine
water, margarine, carrots and onion and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the potato soup, milk, corn, cauliflower, both cheeses and pepper.
Cook until it is serving temperature and enjoy.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook and drain hamburger.
Cook and drain noodles.
Mix cheeses.
In a deep sided 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer the ingredients as follows:
Ragu, noodles, cheeses, hamburger and Ragu, using approximately 1/4 of each ingredient.
Repeat for 3 more layers.
Top with sprinkled Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until well done and bubbly.
Recipe may be divided in half.
Cook one now and freeze one for later.

title: tomato-peach conserve(yields 160 servings)
directions: Scald peaches and tomatoes in boiling water in saucepan. Remove skins and cut into pieces.
Combine with sugar in large, heavy saucepan.
Cook for 3 hours or to desired consistency, stirring frequently with wooden spoon.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Soften cream cheese with mixer.
Add tomato juice and mix well.
Stir in salad dressing.

title: frogs in the hole
directions: Tear a hole big enough to hold an egg in the center of each slice of bread.
Pour oil into skillet, then add bread slices. Break an egg into the hole.
Salt and pepper before frying to desired hardness.
Serve hot with fresh fruit.
Serves 2.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Beat egg for 4 minutes.
Add powdered sugar and margarine; beat for 5 minutes.
Pour this over graham cracker crust and chill 10 minutes.

title: time-saver chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar in a large bowl.
In a pan, bring to a boil the butter, cocoa, shortening and water.
Pour over flour mixture and beat.
Add eggs, cinnamon, vanilla and buttermilk with soda added. Beat well and pour into a greased baking pan (9 x 13 x 2-inch). Bake at 375° until cake springs back when touched, about 45 minutes.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger and chopped onion.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer until thickened.

title: calico beans
directions: Saute hamburger and bacon.
Mix together.
Can add in all 4 cans of beans.
Bake 2 hours at 350°.

title: butter pecan pie
directions: Stir butter to soften and add sugar, slowly beating mixture until fluffy.
Add salt and syrup.
Beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each egg.
Stir in pecans and pour into graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Cool for 3 hours.

title: mennonite sausage
directions: Mix ingredients and roll in 20 rolls.
Wrap in foil and freeze.

title: peach muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add egg and beat well.
Beat in yogurt and vanilla.
Stir in flour and baking powder.
Add peaches and pecans until just blended. Bake for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 12 to 15.

title: sweet and sour brisket
directions: Brown meat on all sides.
Add onions and garlic.
Cook until onions are tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until tender, 3 to 4 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: tuna and potato squares
directions: Shred tuna with fork.
Add eggs and potatoes.
Mix.
Put in baking dish.
Smooth out.
Bake at 375° for about 20 minutes.
Cut into small squares.

title: chalupa
directions: Put all ingredients in large pan.
Cover with water.
Cook 6 hours, covered, at low heat.
Add water as needed.
After 6 hours, take out bones and break up roast.
Cook with lid about 1 hour. Serve this over corn chips and top Chalupa with grated cheese, chopped onions, shredded lettuce, diced tomatoes, diced avocado and taco sauce.

title: tennessee soup
directions: Bring to boil; simmer 40 to 60 minutes.
I add 1/2 cup cooked macaroni after heat is turned off.
It will be cooked in about 6 to 8 minutes.
With the macaroni, this is a complete nutritious meal.
Serves 6.

title: german chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in the boiling water.
Sift flour, sugar, soda and salt together.
Add margarine and buttermilk.
Add and beat until blended egg yolks and vanilla.
Add chocolate mixture and beat until blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layers at 350°.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls.
Refrigerate until firm, then roll in chopped nuts.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Put nuts and coconut in bottom of 9 x 13 pan. Mix cake as directed; pour over nuts and coconut. Combine powdered sugar, cream cheese and margarine. Drop by spoonfuls on batter and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: spiced cider
directions: Tie allspice, cinnamon sticks and cloves in 5-inch square of cotton.
Pour all ingredients in crock-pot or pan.
Place spice bag in; heat.
When hot and ready to serve, put in 3 orange slices.

title: grape-nuts pudding
directions: Pour milk over Grape-Nuts and cool a bit.
Beat egg and add sugar.
Add this and remaining ingredients to Grape-Nuts mixture; stir.
Dot with small pieces of butter.
Bake at 350° until firm and golden brown.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Add the shortening, 1/3 cup buttermilk and mashed bananas; beat for 2 minutes.
Add 1/3 cup more buttermilk and the eggs; beat 2 minutes more.
Fold in the chopped nuts.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) oblong pans at 350° for 45 minutes.
Use Poor Man's Icing.

title: broccoli noodle bake
directions: Melt margarine in large saucepan.
Saute onion, pepper and celery.
Add cooked broccoli.
Meanwhile, cook spaghetti.
In buttered 3-quart casserole, layer spaghetti, vegetable mix and 1 1/2 cups cheese.

title: cherry punch
directions: Chip
frozen
pineapple
juice	until partially thawed. Put in punch
bowl.
Pour Kool-Aid in and ginger ale.
It will be slushy. Good with ice cream added.

title: layered enchilada casserole
directions: Cook beef in 2-quart dish in microwave; drain.
Stir in beans, seasoning mix and 1 cup water.
Cook on High 5 minutes in microwave, stirring once.
Pour sauce into pie plate.
Dip both sides of tortillas in sauce.
Layer beef mixture and dipped tortillas in microwave-safe 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish, cutting tortillas as necessary to fit.
Sprinkle cheese all over top. Cover tightly with plastic wrap.
Cook on Medium-high 10 minutes, turning dish once.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
May garnish with shredded lettuce, chopped tomato and sliced pitted black olives.

title: marinated pork tenderloin
directions: Mix soy sauce, minced onion, white vinegar
and
sugar. Pour over tenderloin and marinate 4 to 5 hours.
Wrap
tenderloin in bacon and bake at 300° for 2 hours uncovered or 1 hour at 350° covered.

title: surprise hot dogs
directions: Grind meat, pepper, cheese, olives and onion together.
Melt butter and use with tomato paste to moisten.
Put in hot dog buns and wrap in foil.
Warm in oven before serving.
Serves about 15 people.

title: hong kong stir-fry
directions: Heat oil in wok or a 10-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add first 4 ingredients.
Cook, stirring, for 2 minutes.
Add next 4 ingredients, stirring for 3 minutes.
Serve over hot, cooked rice. Yields 4 servings with 352 calories per serving.
Preparation time is 30 minutes.

title: baked fruit
directions: Combine apricots, peach slices and pineapple chunks.
Add brown sugar.
Dot with butter and then add crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350°.
Cook until bubbles.
Best served with ham, chicken, turkey, etc.

title: sunday morning pancakes
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in ovenproof pan (pie plate) until it bubbles.
Combine other ingredients (lumpy okay); pour mixture into pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
Sprinkle powdered sugar and/or cinnamon over top.
Bake another 5 minutes.
Cut like pizza and enjoy!
We double the recipe and make 2!

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Beat egg white and add other ingredients.
Drop onto well-greased pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 325°.
Remove from pan when cool.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix together.
Good over tomatoes and salad.

title: apple crisp
directions: Arrange apples in 8 x 1 1/2-inch pan.
Combine oats, sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in butter.
Spread over top.
Bake at 350° until apples are done.

title: steamed sweet potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes.
Cut slits in tops.
Place each potato in a piece of aluminum foil.
Wrap securely.
Place on grill 6 inches from heat, tops down, for 20 minutes.
Turn.
Pierce foil tops with a fork.
Cook for 20 minutes or longer until desired doneness.
Cut foil open.
Combine cloves and butter.
Let stand for 5 minutes.

title: bubble bread
directions: Cut bread
into
cubes and put into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Place
row after row.
Mix other ingredients and pour over bread.
Let rise for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zuetschgenkuchen(prune-plum tart)
directions: Pastry:
Boil eggs for 10 minutes, let cool and rub through a fine sieve.
Mix flour, sugar, 4 egg yolks (sieved), butter and rum.
Roll out and line a 10-inch springform pan.
Refrigerate while preparing plums and topping.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Arrange hamburger on bottom of casserole dish.
Arrange onion on top.
Sprinkle on salt and pepper.
Lay Tater Tots on top.
Add water to soup in small bowl.
Pour soup on top of Tater Tots. Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until hamburger is done.

title: praline bars
directions: On a 12 x 12-inch sheet of foil placed on a cookie sheet, line the crackers in 3 lengthwise rows (7 to a row) so they are touching each other; turn up edges of foil to make a shallow pan. In 1-quart saucepan, stir together margarine and brown sugar until melted and boil mixture 2 minutes.
Take off heat, stir in nuts and pour over crackers.
Spread nuts to edge of crackers.
Bake at 350° until top bubbles (about 5 to 6 minutes).
Cool for 15 minutes.
Break apart.

title: cavitini
directions: Cook pasta to directions.
Drain.
Add pepperoni, onion and green pepper to pasta.
Mix well.
Pour in 13 x 11-inch baking dish.
Cook ground beef and drain.
Add oregano, salt and garlic powder to meat.
Pour meat over pasta, then pour sauce over meat. Add cheese over top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Mix all together and chill.
Great for Christmas!

title: cream puffs
directions: Heat 1 cup water and butter to a rolling boil in saucepan. Stir in flour all at once.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in thoroughly the eggs, one at a time.
Beat mixture until smooth.
Drop large spoonfuls on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until dry at 400°, about 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool slowly.
Cut in half and fill with whipped cream.

title: spiced tea mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Store mixture in an airtight container.
To serve, spoon 1 tablespoon of tea mix in a cup.
Add 6 ounces boiling water, and stir well.
Yield:
18 servings (about 53 calories per 3/4 cup serving).

title: baked hungarian noodles
directions: Cook noodles according to package.
Saute onion, mushrooms and garlic in small amount of oil until onions are clear.
Mix together cooked noodles, sauteed veggies, cottage cheese, yogurt, Worcestershire and Tabasco sauces, poppy seed, salt and pepper in mixing bowl.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Heat the oil in a saucepan over medium heat and add onions and garlic.
Cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.

Add the catsup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce, sugar, chili powder and cayenne to taste (the more cayenne you use, the hotter it will be). Reduce the heat and simmer, partially covered, until the sauce has thickened slightly, about 20 minutes.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes in muffin tins. Refrigerate mix; use as needed.
Will last for weeks.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar and soda together.
Drain 1/2 cup juice from a Number 2 can fruit cocktail.
You won't need the juice.
Add fruit cocktail to beaten egg.
Pour into mixed dry ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch square pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and pecans or walnuts over the batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with whipped cream.
This is easy, quick and very good.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in milk until smooth.
Stir in juice and vanilla. Pour into crust. Chill 3 hours or until set.
Top with desired amount of pie filling before serving.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: ice cream cone cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, egg and half of the water.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Scrape the bowl often (for hand mixing, beat 300 strokes).
Add remaining water and beat 2 minutes longer.
(For hand mixing, beat 300 strokes more.) Spoon about 1/4 cup batter into each cone.
Set cones on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Spoon fluffy pudding frosting over the cakes.
Garnish with sprinkles, if desired.

title: linguini white clam sauce
directions: In large skillet, slightly brown garlic in oil or butter.
Add liquid from clams and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil, add clams and season with salt and pinch of Italian seasoning.
Add garlic to taste, let simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Cook linguini in boiling water until tender, but firm.
Serve sauce over linguini.
Makes 4 servings.

title: season's best shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients and chill.

title: sweetish pecans
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Spread on cookie sheet. Bake in 300° oven just until lightly browned.

title: orange salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese, Cool Whip and jello.
Now blend by hand the pineapple and oranges.
Refrigerate.

title: beef hunter style
directions: In saute pan, add 1/2 olive oil and saute onion, shallots and garlic until they start to brown.
Add mushrooms and cook until done.
Take out of pan.
Hold in warm place on warm plate.

title: michele's scalloped potatoes
directions: Put potatoes in pan; cover with water.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; drain.
Melt margarine.
Mix 2 tablespoons with crumbs. Add flour and seasonings to remaining margarine.
Gradually stir in milk, blending until smooth.
Cook until thick and bubbly.
Layer potatoes and sauce in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle crumbs on top; garnish with parsley.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until tender.

title: banana drop cookies
directions: Drop by teaspoonful on ungreased cookie sheet 1 1/2 inches apart.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes.

title: margaret's chicken casserole
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Use broth from chicken to cook rice.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and almonds over casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: antha's mom's tuna casserole
directions: Mix everything together except shoestring potatoes; then add potatoes.
Put into a greased casserole dish and sprinkle a few potatoes on top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for about 1/2 hour.

title: rich cocoa fudge
directions: Mix sugar, cocoa and salt in heavy 4 qt. sauce pan; stir in milk. Cook over medium heat stirring constantly until mixture comes to full rolling boil. Boil without stirring until mixture reaches 234 fahrenheit on a candy thermometer or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water.

title: summer salad
directions: Prepare vegetables.
Set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients until sugar is dissolved, making a dressing.
Combine with vegetables.
Marinate in refrigerator.
May be made ahead and refrigerated.

title: drop biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm milk.
Stir in egg, sugar and Crisco. Add flour and mix well.
Optional; may add cheese and/or chives. Let set in covered airtight bowl in refrigerator for 1 hour. Spoon in greased muffin pan.
Cook at 425° for 20 minutes or until done.
Leftover dough will keep in refrigerator for several days.

title: chocolate saltine candy
directions: Line jelly roll pan with foil.
Cover with saltines, salt side up.
Boil butter, sugar and vanilla for 3 minutes, until syrupy. Pour over saltines.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes, until foamy and bubbly.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over.
When melted, spread like icing.
Sprinkle broken pecans or coconut on top and spread into chocolate.
Refrigerate 4 to 5 hours or freeze 1 to 2 hours and crack into pieces.

title: cheese roll
directions: Mix together thoroughly and make a long roll.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: hurry-up chocolate cake
directions: Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in greased and floured pan.
Cake will be very moist.

title: peanut sauce
directions: In saucepan, cook onions, garlic, bay leaf and ginger in margarine.
When onion becomes translucent, add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally, or until desired consistency.
Serve over steamed vegetables or pasta.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple.
Add jello and stir until dissolved.
Cool, then add buttermilk, Cool Whip and nuts.
Stir and mix well. Chill.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop onto greased cookie sheet.
Press each cookie lightly with a fork.
Bake for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: creole steak
directions: Salt and pepper the steak.
Roll in flour.
Brown in a small amount of grease.
When brown on both sides, add the onion and tomatoes and juice from the tomatoes.
Simmer on low heat until tender.

title: fried rice
directions: *Cook rice early.
Two cups of raw rice will make 6 cups cooked.

title: strawberry jam nut bread
directions: Cream together the butter, sugar, vanilla and lemon extract. Add the eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Stir together the flour, salt, cream of tartar and baking soda. Add dry ingredients to the creamed mixture alternately with the strawberry jam and sour cream.
Add the walnuts, mixing well. Turn into 2 greased 7 x 5-inch loaf pans and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes or until the loaves test done.
Cool on racks for 10 minutes before removing the loaves from the pans.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add these ingredients to the corn meal mixture and pour over half of the combined mixture into a hot skillet.
Sprinkle cheese and chili peppers over the mixture. Pour remaining mixture over it and bake in 375° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: diet deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in half.
Mix ingredients with egg yolks.

title: mother's pecan pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes in 350° oven.

title: savory succotash
directions: Place all in buttered casserole.
(May stand overnight.)

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, then add the next 3 ingredients.
Then add the rest.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour.

title: holiday nut rolls
directions: Combine Marshmallow Creme and vanilla in mixing bowl and stir with mixing spoon; gradually stir in sugar.
Knead until well blended and shape mixture into 4 rolls, about 1-inch thick in diameter; wrap in plastic and freeze 6 hours.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: In medium saucepan, melt margarine; stir in brown sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil; boil and stir 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and vanilla.
Mix in powdered sugar; beat until smooth.
Spread into buttered 9-inch square baking pan. Chill until firm.
Cut into squares.

title: romme grod
directions: Place 3 cups of cream in a heavy saucepan and heat. Make a thickening with the rest of the cream and as much flour as needed. Let boil a few minutes.
Add the salt.
Stir constantly as it scorches easily.
Serve with cinnamon and sugar in dabs over top, or with milk.
Some use half and half.
We use 3 cups of cream and 1 cup milk.
Otherwise, too rich.

title: homemade mayonnaise
directions: Break the egg into a blender.
Cover and blend at high speed for 30 seconds.
Add the dry mustard, salt, lemon juice and honey and blend again at high speed for 15 to 20 seconds.
While the blender is still running, add the oil in a very slow steady stream.
As the mayonnaise thickens, you will have to stop
the blender and stir some of the oil in, then turn the blender back on high.
With a spatula, scrape the emulsion toward the blades. Makes 1/2 cup.

title: anytime broccoli cheese sauce
directions: Combine soup and milk. Conventional: Over medium heat, until hot and bubbling, stirring often. Microwave: Microwave, uncovered, on high 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring halfway through heating.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all together and pour into pie crusts. Bake at 350° for about 35 minutes. Makes 2 pies.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar, add egg yolks and beat well.
Add bananas.
Add flour sifted with salt and baking powder.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add soda last with a little of the buttermilk.
Add egg whites.
Bake at 350°.

title: spinach salad
directions: In a bowl, combine spinach, bacon, eggs, avocado, and mushrooms.
In another bowl or jar, combine oil, vinegar, honey, etc. (except red onions) and mix well.
Pour over greens just before serving and toss well.
Garnish with onion rings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook 1/2 hour over stove, stirring last minute.
Add vanilla. Sprinkle top with cinnamon.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos with rolling pin or in food processor.
Set aside. In a medium bowl, cream butter, cheese and sugar together until light and fluffy.
In a separate bowl, mix pudding mix and milk together; stir until thoroughly mixed.
Add pudding mixture to cream mixture; beat until well mixed.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In an oblong serving dish, layer crushed cookies, cream and pudding mixture, ending with cookies.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: tuna-broccoli casserole(microwave)
directions: Place broccoli in a 10 x 6 x 1 3/4-inch baking dish. Cover with plastic wrap.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until defrosted.
Drain.
Mix together soup, eggs, mushrooms, onion and olives.
Place a layer of tuna and sauce mixture over broccoli. Sprinkle with cracker crumbs.
Microwave on Medium-high (70%) for 12 to 15 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Let stand 5 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Place on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine egg, soups, mayonnaise and lemon.
Pour over chicken.
Sprinkle cheese over soup mixture.
Melt oleo and add to stuffing.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: navajo fry bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together into a large mixing bowl. Add 1 cup lukewarm water to flour mixture. Using hands, mix until dough is firm, but not hard. If dough becomes hard, more water may be added. Turn portion of dough out onto floured board and roll out to 1/4-inch thick, then cut into 3-inch squares. Fry in deep fat heated to 400°. Drain on absorbent paper.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix together peaches and 1/2 cup of sugar and pour into cake pan.
Mix together flour, 1 cup sugar, milk, butter and baking powder.
Pour over peaches and sugar.
Do not stir!!
Bake at 375° until golden brown. It is delicious!!!

title: egg custard
directions: Add eggs, sugar, butter and flour.
Mix well.
Then add milk and flavoring.
Pour into 8-inch pie shell; bake at 350° until brown.

title: chunky fruit salad
directions: Drain juice from oranges and dissolve pudding in juice.
Cut fruit in bite size pieces.
Pour pudding mixture over fruit. Refrigerate before serving.

title: texas cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt and baking soda in a bowl.
Bring to a boil, butter, water and cocoa.
Add to first mixture, then immediately add sour cream, eggs and vanilla.
Pour into greased sheet pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
(Do not overbake.)

title: sausage gravy
directions: Add 2 cups milk to sausage; break up sausage to bite-size.
Add peppers and salt; cook until brown.
Add flour and whip roux until firm.
Stir in remaining milk slowly, making sure all clumps of rue are broken.
Cook over high heat until thick, stirring constantly.

title: angel pie
directions: Cook pineapple and marshmallows in top of double boiler until marshmallows are melted.
Cool mixture.
Add strawberries.
Chill milk, bowl and beaters thoroughly, then whip milk until stiff. Add to cooled pineapple mixture and mix well.
Pour into cooled pie shell and refrigerate for several hours.

title: chocolate, oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt margarine (low-heat).
Add sugar, cocoa and milk.
Heat to full boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, oats and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonful on waxed paper or aluminum foil.

title: banana tapioca pudding
directions: In a saucepan, combine milk, tapioca, sugar, and egg.
Let stand 5 min.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a full boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and bananas. Cool for 20 min. Serve warm or cold.
Yields: 6 servings.

title: pineapple-orange cooler
directions: In each of 6 chilled glasses, place 1 small scoop of the sherbet.
Combine pineapple juice, orange juice and bitters.
To each glass, add a small amount of the juice mixture.
Stir to muddle.
Divide remaining juice mixture among glasses.
Add another scoop of sherbet to each glass.
Fill with carbonated beverage.
Garnish with orange slices.
Makes 6 servings.
Great on a hot summer day!

title: festive veggie pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread crescent rolls out in large cookie sheet.
Press seams together.
Bake until light golden brown, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Beat together cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread on cooled crust.
Cut gently into squares.
Sprinkle chopped onion on each one. Then place pieces of tomato and broccoli on each square. Chill.

title: debby heidenreich's scotch eggs
directions: Mix mustard with beaten egg.
Cut sausage in 6 equal parts. Wrap around eggs.
Dip in flour and egg mixture and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry until brown.
Cut in half.
Serve warm with mustard sauce (Hellmann's Dijonaise is good.)

title: brown sugar chews
directions: Blend
egg
and
sugar well.
Add flour, salt, soda and walnuts.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes in greased 8-inch pan.

title: tee kays scrumptious meat loaf
directions: *Use the celery salt if you use the cream of celery soup, but you can use about 2 ounces to 4 ounces of chopped mushrooms if you decide to use the cream of mushroom soup.

title: crisp oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Beat in sugars until creamy.
Beat in eggs and extracts.
Add dry ingredients in order listed and at last add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° to 375° until light brown, about 7 to 10 minutes.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Mix and make into a roll.
Set in cool place overnight. Slice and bake.

title: hamburger corn bake
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: honeyed chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a
greased pan skin side up.
Combine all other ingredients; mix well.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Baste every 15 minutes with sauce until chicken is tender and nicely browned.

title: low-fat eggnog
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Mix well and chill at least 4 hours.
Makes 10 servings.

title: applesauce meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients.
Knead mixture with hands until well blended.
Pack into loaf pan.
Top with Healthy Choice pasta sauce.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more.
Serves 8.
Serving Amount:
1 portion. Exchanges:
3 meat and 1 bread.
Calories:

title: twinkie cake
directions: Cut Twinkies in half.
Line bottom of dish.
Mix pudding as directed on box.
Cover Twinkies with a layer of sliced bananas. Spread pudding over bananas.
Cover with Cool Whip and refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water; add cold water, bananas, pineapple and marshmallows and congeal.

title: cowboy beans
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add all ingredients; bake until desired consistency.
Use green pepper, onion, salt, pepper and cinnamon to taste.

title: taco salad
directions: Toss taco mix with cooled hamburger.
Add chopped onion, grated cheese, drained beans, tomato and lettuce.
Just before serving, toss in dressing and chips on top.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; stir in sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until thick and lemon-colored.
Stir in zucchini.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and cinnamon; add to the mixture and mix.

title: white chocolate cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Put chocolate wafers in blender & blend until crumbs form. Mix crumbs with 4 Tbsp. margarine and press into bottom and about 2 inches up sides of a 10 x 2 1/2 inch spring form pan that has been greased. Set aside.

In a heavy saucepan over low heat melt white chocolate until smooth, stirring occasionally. In large bowl with mixer on low speed combine cream cheese and 1/2 c. margarine until smooth. Add melted white chocolate, eggs, sugar and vanilla, beat just until smooth. Pour mixture into pan with chocolate crust and bake for 1 hour. Cool on wire rack and refrigerate at least 4 hours before serving.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat shortening and sugar until creamy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Blend in flour mixture.
Stir in oats.
Chill.
Shape dough into balls about 1-inch in diameter.
Place about 2 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for only about 10 minutes for soft chewy cookies, longer for crunchy cookies.
Remove from baking sheet while warm.
Yield:
3 to 4 dozen.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Put hash brown potatoes in 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Place dish on cookie sheet.

title: okra puffs
directions: Boil in a small amount of water until tender; drain.
Chop, mash and beat with a fork or in a blender.
Add egg, sugar, salt and pepper.
Beat well.
Stir flour and baking powder together. Add and beat.
Drop by 1 teaspoon into deep, very hot fat.
Brown; turn without pricking.
Cook until very brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.
Serves 8 or more.
If puffs are not small round shapes, more flour may be needed.
Batter keeps well in refrigerator several days.

title: grilled ranch bread
directions: Combine butter and dressing and mix.
Spread on bread and toast.

title: 8 pounds baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight until soft, but not mushy.
Drain.
Mix the rest of the ingredients except bacon in pan and cook. Cook bacon and cut into pieces. Add bacon to the mixture at the end of cooking.
Pour over beans.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix well together. Spread on pan.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion in boiling salt water 5 minutes; drain. Add soup, sour cream and carrots.
Combine stuffing mix and oleo. Spread 1/2 into 12 x 7 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mix on top, then add remaining stuffing mix and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken scampi(scaled for 4 servings)
directions: Combine
everything but the chicken and simmer together while you cut up the chicken breasts into fairly small pieces. Put everything	into
a casserole and cover.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove cover and brown under broiler.

title: scones
directions: Whisk together eggs, milk and oil.
Add to flour and baking powder; mix well.
Pat out on floured board and cut.
Place closely together on cookie sheet.
Bake 5 to 10 minutes at 450° to 500°.

title: sweet pickles - quick and easy
directions: Wash cucumbers and put into jars.
To each quart add the salt, mustard seed and celery seed.
Mix the water, vinegar and sugar. Heat this mixture and pour into filled jars.
Cold pack for 5 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Be careful in your selection.
Do not choose too young and take only such as have been reared in a good moral atmosphere.
Some insist on keeping them in a pickle while others keep them in hot water.
This only makes them sour, hard and bitter.
Even a poor variety may be made sweet, tender and good by garnishing them with patience, well-sweetened with smiles and flavored with kisses to taste.
Then wrap them in a mantle of charity.
Keep them warm with a steady fire of domestic devotion and serve with 3 good meals a day.
When thus prepared, they will keep for years.

title: rice croquettes
directions: Wash rice. Cook according to package. Don't overcook.
Mix all ingredients. Form small ovals.
Fry in hot oil. Drain and serve hot.

title: apple spice cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter and flour a 9-inch tube or 12 cup Bundt pan.
Stir flour, baking powder, soda and spices with fork in bowl.
Combine apples, raisins and walnuts in another bowl.
Add 3 tablespoons of flour mixture.
Toss to coat and set aside.

title: applesauce loaf
directions: Cream shortening, brown sugar and egg together.

Add applesauce, soda, salt, cinnamon and cloves. Add flour and raisins. Pour into greased and floured loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a wooden pick tester comes out clean. Yield: One loaf.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add peanut butter and milk and mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour in crust and freeze. Take out 15 minutes before serving.

title: hearty italian soup
directions: Brown sausage, green pepper and onion; drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients except macaroni and cheese.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in macaroni, cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve with cheese sprinkled on top.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix well.
Melt 1/2 cup margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cornbread mixture on melted margarine.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot cranberry punch
directions: Put spices in basket of coffee percolator pot and juices in the pot.
Perk.

title: linguine and artichokes in white sauce
directions: In large, heavy skillet, heat 1/4 cup olive oil and 1/4 cup butter over moderately low heat.
Add flour and cook mixture, stirring, for 3 minutes.
Stir in chicken stock and cook over moderately high heat for 1 minute.
Add garlic, lemon juice, parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook for 5 minutes over low heat, stirring occasionally.

Add artichoke hearts, 2 tablespoons Parmesan cheese and drained capers; cook, covered, for 8 minutes. In large casserole, combine 2 tablespoons olive oil, 1 tablespoon Parmesan cheese, softened butter and 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Add drained linguine to the casserole and toss with the cheese mixture. Divide pasta among 4 heated bowls; top with sauce and garnish each serving with additional grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: original toll house chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine dry goods and liquid goods in separate bowls.
Drop the dough onto ungreased cookie sheets. Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 5 dozen 2 1/4-inch cookies.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef at medium heat.
Season as desired.
Drain and cool.
Toss chopped lettuce, tomatoes and cheese in a large bowl.
Add Catalina dressing.
Add ground beef.
Toss well.
Crush tortilla chips and sprinkle on top of salad.
Serves 12 to 15 people.

title: vinaigrette dressing
directions: Whisk the oil and vinegar together, adding the oil slowly to the vinegar.

title: lime cabbage salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in the hot water, then add the cold water. Mix remaining ingredients and blend into gelatin.
Pour into mold and chill.

title: aunt audrey's cheese log
directions: Mix well together.
Roll in one long roll or 2 small rolls. Roll in chili powder and chopped nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap; refrigerate several hours before serving.
Slice as needed.
Serve with crackers.

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, nuts and flour together in a large bowl. Stir in the butter; mix with your hands until crumbly.
Remove 1 cup of the mixture to be used later as a topping.
Press remainder in an 8-inch square pan; press firmly.
Bake at 350° for about 12 to 15 minutes.
Beat the cream cheese until smooth with the granulated sugar.
Beat in the egg, lemon juice, cream and vanilla.
Pour this into the baked crust.
Top with the reserved crumbs.
Return to oven; bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into 2-inch squares.
Refrigerate.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Mix together cake mix, 1/3 cup evaporated milk, melted butter and nuts.
Put 1/2 batter in 9 x 13-inch greased pan and bake 6 minutes at 350°.

title: apple-cheese spread
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer until smooth.
Refrigerate. Serve with wheat crackers.

title: pickle peach salad
directions: Heat pickle juice and add jello, stirring until dissolved. Mix in remaining ingredients and chill before serving.

title: brownies
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add melted chocolate.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour minus 1 tablespoon, baking powder and salt.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites, vanilla and pecans which have been mixed with reserved flour.
Roll into a 9 x 13-inch pan which has been greased on the sides only and lined with brown paper.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool.
Turn out on waxed paper.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cut into squares.

title: sausage breakfast loaf
directions: In a large skillet, saut the sausage; cool. In a bowl, combine the sausage, cheese, 1 egg that has been scrambled, parsley, onion salt and garlic salt; mix well.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Mix
shortening, butter, brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
Sift in flour and salt.
Roll in walnut size balls. Mix 1 egg white slightly.
Dip balls in egg white and roll in nuts.
Bake 1 inch apart for 5 minutes in a 350° oven.
Take from oven.
Press thumbprint and bake 8 minutes longer.
Fill with strawberry preserves.

title: sausage-wild rice casserole
directions: Add sausage to rice.
Add water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Cook sausage in a large skillet until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well; set aside.
Combine cheese and soup in a heavy Dutch oven; cook over medium heat, stirring until cheese melts.
Add sausage, picante sauce and milk; mix well.
Transfer mixture to a chafing dish.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: apple-mallow bake
directions: Place apples, raisins and water in baking dish.
Mix flour, sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Cut in oleo until crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with marshmallows.
Broil until brown.

title: never fail egg custard
directions: Scald milk, salt and sugar until it beads.
Pour over eggs; add vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 325° until firm and knife comes out clean.
Sprinkle with nutmeg if desired.

title: chicken stir-up
directions: In large electric skillet, saute chicken breast in butter.
Add onion, mushrooms and garlic.
Add tomatoes, butter beans and green beans.
This is a quick 1-dish meal.
As soon as chicken is cooled, add remaining ingredients until hot.
Serve with sourdough or corn bread.

title: blarney brunch
directions: Cook corn according to directions.
Open pouch and drain butter sauce into small skillet.
Saute onion until transparent. Add sausage and lightly brown, about 5 minutes.

title: banana split cake
directions: For crust, mix 1 stick oleo with graham crackers.
Line bottom of pan with mixture.

title: california casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
In hot butter in large skillet, saute onion until golden, about 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in hot rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly to mix well.
Layer half the rice mixture in bottom of baking dish, then half the chiles.
Sprinkle with half the cheese.
Repeat the layers.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes, or until bubbly and hot. Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil and eggs; mix well.
Mix in apples and nuts. Do not beat.
Bake in tube pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: golden twice baked potatoes
directions: Cut lengthwise slice from top of each potato; scoop out potato, leaving 1/8-inch shell.
Combine potato, 1 cup cheese, salad dressing, milk, egg and seasonings.
Beat until fluffy. Fill shells; top with remaining cheese, onion and bacon bits. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Pack eggs in a jar, alternating with onion slices.
Heat water, vinegar, salt and spices to boiling point.
Pour hot solution over eggs.
Store in refrigerator for 36 hours before eating.

title: sweet salties
directions: Melt chocolate and shortening in heavy saucepan over low flame.
Add pretzels and peanuts; mix well.
Spread into a buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Chill 20 minutes or until firm.
Break into pieces.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in large bowl.
Add sugar, oil, eggs and mix well.
Add carrots, nuts, coconut and pineapple; blend well.
Bake in 10-inch tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 16 servings.

title: chicken savannah
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Add soup and sauce.
Place chicken in casserole dish, turning several times to coat.
Cover and cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease 12 (3-inch) muffin pan cups.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, salt and cloves.
Add blueberries; toss to coat with flour mixture.
Set aside.
Melt butter; cool slightly, then add yogurt, egg, lemon rind and lemon and vanilla extracts.
Beat until blended.
Stir yogurt mixture into flour-berry mixture just until blended; do not overmix.
Divide batter among muffin pan cups.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 12.

title: tomato pie
directions: Cook pie shell according to directions.
Put a layer of sliced tomatoes on bottom; sprinkle with salt and pepper, basil and chives.
Layer again.
Combine mayonnaise and cheese and spread on top, sealing all edges.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: m&m brownies
directions: Mix brownie mix as directed on package.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan or jelly roll size pan (as desired), greased.
Mix oleo, brown sugar and oatmeal; sprinkle over unbaked brownie batter and add M&M's over all.
Can use plain or peanut.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: aunt sue's sunshine pudding
directions: Reach out the window, get a ray of sunshine and mix all together.
Top with a thick layer of God's love.
Cut into great big chunks and pass around.

title: apple stuffing
directions: In a 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, melt margarine. Add onions, celery and apples. Cook 4-5 minutes, stirring frequently, until softened. Remove from heat; stir in stuffing mix and seasonings. Add cider, stirring just to moisten.
Yields 14 cups.

title: spinach in phyllo (filo)
directions: Squeeze all water from spinach.
Grate cheese and mix with eggs, spinach and black pepper.
Following directions on phyllo dough package, layer 1/2 the pastry with sweet butter.
Put filling in center and put top layer of pastry on.
Bake for 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: cream filling
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients; add the scalded milk gradually. Cook over low heat until it thickens, stirring constantly, and continue the cooking, over hot water, for 15 minutes.

title: tex-mex corn muffins
directions: Heat ungreased muffin pans in 400° oven for 10 minutes. Combine corn meal, soda and salt.
Stir in pimiento, cheese, onion, green chilies and garlic.
Make a well in center of mixture.
Combine eggs, milk and corn.
Add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pans immediately.
Yields 1 1/2 dozen.

title: maui chicken
directions: Cut chicken into serving pieces; arrange in shallow pan. Cover and seal tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together.
Blend dry ingredients and add to zucchini mixture.
Pour into greased loaf pans (makes 2) and bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine; add mushrooms, consomme and rice. Bake in casserole at 350° for about 1 hour.
Do not cover; do not stir.

title: appetizing crab ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts; form into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts; chill to set.
Serve with Triscuits or other crackers.

title: adam's fruit cocktail
directions: Put fruit in a bowl.
Put 3 spoonfuls of whipped cream and stir until it is stirred enough.
After, you'll have your homemade fruit cocktail.
Makes one serving.

title: dill weed dip(for veggies)
directions: Dissolve 2 cups lime in a gallon of water.
Slice cucumbers. Pour mixture over the sliced cucumbers and soak overnight.
The next day, wash out the lime.
Soak in clear water 1 hour or so. Wash good.
Put 1 teaspoon alum in each quart of hot water until they are covered. Soak for 1 hour.
Put in ice water.
Let set until you get the vinegar mixture fixed.
Mix 1 cup sugar to 1 cup vinegar and spices to taste.
Heat this mixture and pour back over the cucumbers for 2 mornings. The third morning, pack in jars and seal.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut round steak in small cubes.
Set aside.
Chop bell pepper and onion.
In a large nonstick skillet, put 2 tablespoons oil; let it get hot.
Add round steak; saute until brown.
Add bell pepper and onion.
In a cup, place 3/4 cup water, 4 tablespoons soy sauce and 1/4 teaspoon ginger; stir.
Add to skillet; simmer until meat is tender.
Serve over rice.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375 degrees.
Mix well shortening, sugar, egg, flavoring.
Mix flour and salt and stir in.
Divide dough in half. Blend red food coloring into one half.
Roll one teaspoon each colored dough on lightly floured board into a strip four inches long.
Place strips side by side, press lightly together and twist like a rope.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Leave top down for handle of cane.
Bake nine minutes or until lightly browned. Remove while still warm.
Sprinkle with mixture of half cup crushed peppermint stick candy and half cup sugar.

title: cauliflower parmesan
directions: Cook and drain cauliflower.
Melt butter; stir in basil.
Pour over cauliflower; toss lightly.
Add cheese; toss lightly until cauliflower is coated.
Sprinkle bread crumbs over cauliflower.

title: smithfield ham and crab casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut off a few large slices of ham and place on the bottom of a casserole dish.
Cover with about 1-inch of cooked crabmeat.
Add a top layer of ham slices.
Place in a 350° oven.
Cook for about 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Have cream cheese and margarine at room temperature.
Beat in sifted powdered sugar; add extract.
Spread on cake.
Leave plain or sprinkle with finely chopped nuts.

title: corn bread beef bake
directions: In a skillet, cook beef over medium heat until no longer pink. Drain. Add the beans, ketchup, brown sugar and pepper. Mix well. Transfer to a greased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish.

title: dago cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage with onion, then add hamburger meat (drained), then add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes.

title: honey walnut mazurka
directions: In a large bowl, combine all-purpose flour, instant flour and baking powder.
Cut butter into small pieces; add to mixture. Blend until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add sugar, yolks, sour cream and vanilla; knead into
a smooth dough.
Cover bowl; refrigerate overnight.
In bowl, combine walnuts and powdered sugar.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Divide dough into thirds.
On a lightly floured surface, roll one part to a 13 x 9-inch rectangle. Line bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch pan with waxed paper.
Place rolled dough in pan.
Spread 2/3 cup apricot preserves over dough. Sprinkle one cup walnut mixture over apricot.
Drizzle 4 teaspoons honey over walnuts.
Roll 2nd part of dough into 13 x 9-inch.
Place on top of first layer; press gently to smooth. Repeat filling over 2nd layer.
Repeat with 3rd layer of dough and filling.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool. Makes 20 to 24 servings.

title: caushaw pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into crusts.
Bake 20 minutes at 450°; reduce heat to 400° and bake until firm.
Makes two 9-inch pies.

title: broccoli with mornay sauce
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until almost tender.
Refresh under cold water; drain well.

title: meatballs 'n rice
directions: Shape ground beef into meatballs.
Brown in melted butter in skillet. Add salt, spaghetti sauce and water. Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Move meatballs to the side of the skillet. Bring liquid to a boil and stir in rice. Cover and remove from heat. Allow to stand 5 minutes. Serves 4.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Pour water over oats and raisins and let stand 20 minutes. Cream 1 cup brown sugar, granulated sugar, oil and eggs together. Add flour, soda, salt and cinnamon.
Pour in water, oat and raisin mixture and stir.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage breakfast dish
directions: Saute mushrooms with sausage and drain.
Place bread cubes in a greased casserole dish (12 x 8 x 2-inch) and top with sausage and Cheddar cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, celery seed and oregano. Pour over all.
Refrigerate for 8 hours or overnight.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: fresh mint punch
directions: Bring sugar and 5 cups water to a boil in saucepan.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Add orange rind and mint leaves.
Let stand, covered, for 2 hours.
Strain.
Add fruit juices and food coloring.
Mix well.
Add ginger ale.
Pour over crushed ice.

title: mr. v's breakfast
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Cut out center of bread with a biscuit cutter.
Put bread in pan.
Crack open egg and put egg in the center of bread.
Cook
until egg starts to get done.
Turn and cook on the other side until done.

title: succotash
directions: In a saucepan combine all ingredients except cream and flour with 1/2 cup water.
Cover and simmer 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Remove salt pork if used.
Slowly blend in cream and flour; stir well.
Cook and stir until thickened (if cream sauce is desired).

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Add remaining ingredients; cook on low heat until cheese melts.
Stir often.
Serve warm with corn chips.

title: joyce's cheese cake
directions: Mix together and spread in an 8 x 12-inch glass pan, lightly greased.

title: party salad
directions: Stir all together in large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate.
Nice holiday salad!

title: pie crust
directions: Mix all together.
Any leftover can be frozen.

title: pick-up sandwiches
directions: Split bread lengthwise and butter both pieces.
Mix salad dressing, pimiento, garlic powder, India relish and salt and pepper to taste.
Spread mixture on bread and slightly toast at 350°.
Cut crosswise into pieces.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift first 5 ingredients together, then add yeast to the flour.
Cut in shortening.
Add warm water to buttermilk.
Combine dry ingredients with liquid ingredients and mix to sticky dough. Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.
Roll out and cut.
Let rise 30 minutes.
Brush tops with margarine.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Yields 4 1/2 dozen.

title: pepper steak
directions: Partially freeze meat and cut into strips 3-inches long and 1/4 inch wide.
In large skillet brown meat in hot Crisco.
Drain excess fat.
Drain tomatoes, reserving liquid.

Add reserved liquid, water, onions, garlic, salt and pepper to meat in skillet. Cover and simmer 50 to 60 minutes or until thick and bubbly. Uncover and stir in Worcestershire sauce, flour and gravy mixture. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Cut green pepper into 2-inch long strips and add to meat along with tomatoes (cut up).
Simmer 5 minutes longer and serve over hot rice.

title: pigs in a blanket
directions: Preheat oven as directed on package of crescent rolls.
Cut crescent rolls in half and cut hot dogs in half.
(If using Lil' Smokies, use whole.)
Wrap hot dogs in crescent rolls.
Place on cookie sheet and bake as directed on crescent roll package.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat all ingredients in order.
Fold in 2 cups sour cream. Pour in an ungreased 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour, then at 250° for 1 hour, and turn oven off and leave 1 hour.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Lightly coat bottom of 9 x 13 pan with cooking spray. Press 1 of the 2 rolls of dough onto the bottom of pan. Mix other ingredients till smooth. Pour over dough. Slice other roll of dough and place over cream cheese mixture. Bake at 350 for 40 minutes. Let cool before cutting.

title: vegetable ball
directions: Drain pineapple (squeeze out with hands).
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Serve as a dip, or roll into a ball and serve with crackers.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream oleo with sugar.
Add sour cream.
Blend together.
Add eggs; blend.
Add flour, baking soda and vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour into large bundt pan that has been greased and floured.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes at preheated 325° oven.

title: oysters crackers
directions: Mix together.
Bake 45 minutes at 250°.
Stir a couple of times.

title: party chicken
directions: Bake at 325° for 60 minutes or until celery and onions are done.

title: lima bean casserole
directions: Cook lima beans according to the directions on package.
Slice carrots and onions.
Cook in boiling water until carrots are semi-soft; save broth.
In saucepan, combine butter, flour, broth and cut up Velveeta cheese.
Stir over medium heat until melted. Alternate sauce and vegetables in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Toss apples with lemon and water; put in baking dish.
In large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar, nutmeg and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Cut in margarine and add nuts.
Crumble over apples to cover completely.
Do not pack down.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; bake in a 1-quart casserole dish at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: grilled cheese
directions: Put the cheese between 2 slices of bread.
Butter the outsides of the sandwich and brown in a skillet on the stove.

title: turnip casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Use 2 tablespoons of butter to make buttered crumbs; set aside. Peel and slice turnips; cover with water and bring to the boil. Cook for 1 to 2 minutes; drain. Add more water and cook for 15 to 16 minutes. Drain and mash. Beat in the cream cheese, salt, pepper, sugar and the remaining butter; mix well.
Pour into a greased casserole and cover with the buttered crumbs. Bake until hot and lightly browned, about 15 to 20 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Heat to boiling in crock-pot and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine fruits, nuts and marshmallows.
Fold in whipped cream. Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: butter cookies
directions: Cream
margarine and sugar.
Add the remaining ingredients. Roll
out.
Cut
into desired shapes.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: batter for fried onion rings
directions: Beat egg; add water and stir in dry ingredients.
Mix well. Dip onion rings into batter and fry in hot deep vegetable oil for 2 or 3 minutes each side until golden brown.
