Drain on paper towel and salt.
This is a good batter for deep frying anything, especially such vegetables as mushrooms, cauliflower, squash, bell pepper strips as well as shrimp.

title: patti's chili spread
directions: Spread cream cheese out on a cookie sheet or pizza pan.
Pour sauce over it and spread.
Top with finely chopped green pepper, green olives, black olives and Mozzarella cheese.
Serve with Fritos.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Brown vermicilli in butter until golden brown.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Add rice; bring to boil again, then cover and turn to low and cook for 20 minutes.
Stir in pepper and serve.
Excellent with flank steak.
Serves 4.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins in water until all the water is boiled out.
Add the applesauce, sweetener, oil and eggs; mix well.
Blend in flour, soda, cinnamon and vanilla.
Pour the mixture into a greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until cake is done.

title: my favorite sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Chill 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 400°. Roll dough out 1/8-inch thick onto powdered sugar surface.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 to 8 minutes, or until edges begin to brown on edges.
Frost with powdered sugar and milk icing.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt, Cool Whip and fruit together; pour into pie crust. Freeze until ready to serve.
Top with additional Cool Whip if desired.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Line greased oblong pan with slightly crushed Doritos. Mix soups, tomatoes and onion. Put into blender and mix well. Pour into bowl and add chicken. Mix. Pour very slowly into pan. Add more Doritos on top. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pizza and rice soup
directions: Combine sausage, bell pepper, and onion in soup pot.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes or until sausage is fully cooked and vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients except for garnish.
Cook over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Sprinkle additional cheese over top of each serving.
Makes about 8 servings.

title: wild rice waldorf salad
directions: Dice the unpared apples and toss with the mixture of lemon juice and brown sugar.
Stir in celery and wild rice.
Blend the mayonnaise with the sour cream and toss.
Chill thoroughly, but not longer than 6 to 8 hours.
Add peanuts just before serving. Serves 6.

title: hamburger stew
directions: Brown the hamburger and diced onion with a dash of salt.
Dice the potatoes, celery and carrots into 1-inch cubes; cook with a dash of salt just until done.
Drain.
Add the soup and 1/2 can water.

title: strawberry and banana dip
directions: Mix altogether.
Good dip for most fruits.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Brown ground beef.
Add sugar, salt, pepper and tomato sauce.
Cook 5 minutes.
Soften cream cheese with sour cream.
Put 1/2 noodles on bottom of baking dish.
Add 1/2 meat mixture and 1/2 cream cheese mixture; repeat.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Cook 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken pie
directions: In a 3-quart pan in butter, cook onion and celery until tender. Stir in soup, milk and Worcestershire sauce until blended.
Add chicken, vegetables and potatoes.
Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Spoon into a 2-quart oval or 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Set aside.
Roll pastry dough 1-inch larger than dish.
With knife cut pastry into 3/4-inch strips.
Crisscross over mixture to form lattice top.
Crimp edges and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: my miracle salad
directions: Soften Knox gelatine in cold water.
Dissolve the Jell-O in boiling water.
Combine gelatine and Jell-O.
Allow to cool.
Add fruit cocktail.
Soften cheese with Cool Whip.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate to congeal.
Serve on lettuce with mayonnaise.

title: transparent pie
directions: Beat together egg yolks and sugar.
Place in medium saucepan over low heat.
Melt butter in egg mixture, stirring constantly. Remove from heat as soon as butter melts.
Add evaporated milk and vanilla.
Pour into crust and bake for 15 minutes at 400°.
Then reduce heat and bake until custard is set.
Cover pie with meringue made from 4 egg whites and 8 tablespoons of sugar. Return to oven to brown meringue.
Watch carefully.

title: banana nut bread #1
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inch).
Mix all ingredients.
Beat 30 seconds.
Pour into pan. Bake until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean, 55 to 60 minutes. Cool slightly.
Loosen sides of loaf from pan.
Remove from pan. Cool completely before slicing.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles according to directions on package.
Cook butter, cream and Parmesan cheese together on low for 5 to 7 minutes.
Add bacon; serve over cooked noodles.
Toss into noodles and serve with extra grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 8.

title: mock homemade chile beans
directions: Cook hamburger; drain.
Add diced onions (1 cup), cooked.
Add Dennison's contents and simmer.

title: thelma's ripe cucumber pickles
directions: Wash, peel, slice cucumbers lengthwise and remove seeds.
Cut in large chunks.
Cover with brine made of alum, salt and 1 quart of water.
Bring gradually to boil then set back on stove or under low heat for 2 hours.
Cook slowly until transparent and crisp, not overcooked.
Drain well.
Let set until cold.
Put the cloves and cinnamon in a cheesecloth bag.
Tie around with string.
Make syrup of brown sugar, vinegar, and spices.
In a glass, stainless steel, or enamel pan, pour the syrup over the cucumbers.
The next 3 successive mornings, drain the syrup, reheat and pour back over the cucumbers.
The last morning put in clean hot jars and seal.

title: cream cheese dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese and Miracle Whip.
Cut up green onions and lunch meat into small pieces.
Refrigerate overnight. Serve with crackers or chips.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Cream potato and butter together.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake for 45 minutes at 375°.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy; add sugar and beat.
Add remaining ingredients except the sesame or poppy seed.
Line 2 loaf pans with wax paper.
Pour in batter and cover top with sesame seed or poppy seed.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes before removing.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Combine sugar, evaporated milk and caramels.
Cook and stir over medium high heat until all over boil.
Boil 5 minutes, stirring continuously.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour into a buttered 8-inch square pan.

title: cream puffs
directions: Filling:
Custard, instant pudding or ice cream (your choice).

title: strawberry salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine gelatin and water, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in strawberries and pineapple. Fold in bananas.
Pour 1/2 of mixture in a large serving dish. Chill this and remaining mixture until partially set.
Then spread sour cream over mixture in serving dish and top with remaining mixture.
Chill until completely set.

title: pan roasted vegetables
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt butter in oven.
Stir in thyme.
Add remaining ingredients, toss and coat; cover with foil.
Bake for 25 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Season to taste.

title: quick and easy scalloped potatoes
directions: Parboil potatoes until just tender with skins on.
In saucepan, heat all other ingredients.
Pour hot liquid over sliced potatoes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Top with ham or bacon slices (optional).
Bake until potatoes are done at 350°.

title: german sour cream twists
directions: Sift flour and salt into mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening. Dissolve yeast in water.
Stir into flour mixture with sour cream, eggs and vanilla; mix well.
Cover with a damp cloth and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Roll half of dough on sugared board into oblong 8 x 16 inches.
Fold ends to center; sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Roll again and repeat for a 3rd time.
Roll about 1/2 inch thick and cut into 1 x 4-inch strips.
Twist ends in opposite directions and make into shape of horse shoes.

title: beef tenderloin picnic sandwiches
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Mix well.
Place tenderloin on a rack in a roasting pan. Brush with butter mixture.
Insert meat thermometer, making sure it does not touch fat.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 45 minutes or until thermometer registers 140° for rare, 150° for medium-rare or 160° for medium.
Slice tenderloin.
Serve on party rolls with sour cream and prepared horseradish.
Yields 16 to 20 servings.

title: quick easy rolls
directions: Combine first three ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon batter into muffin pans, coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly brown.

title: microwave chicken salad bake
directions: Spread pecans in a 9-inch pie plate.
Microwave at 100% (High) for 2 to 3 minutes or until toasted; stir after 1 minute.

title: double corn bread
directions: Heat oven
to
Grease 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Blend all ingredients
except
corn about 20 seconds, then beat for about one
minute.
Stir	in
corn
(drained
if you use whole kernel). Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: indian corn pudding
directions: Scald milk and combine with corn, brown sugar, flour and butter.
Add egg yolks, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into corn mixture.
Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Place dish in a pan of simmering water and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: spring daffodil salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water in bowl.
Drain fruit well; reserve syrups.
Combine 1 cup reserved syrup and jello.
Chill, stirring twice, until slightly thickened.
Fold in peaches and pineapple.
Fold in marshmallows.
Turn into rinsed 9 x 13-inch salad pan. Chill until firm.
Spread with Cheese Topping.

title: quick lemon pie
directions: Mix juice and milk.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell. Chill for 2 to 3 hours and serve.

title: peanut brittle(microwave)
directions: Place sugar, corn syrup and water in 2-quart casserole.
Cook on High in microwave (750 watts) 5 minutes.
Stir.
Add peanuts. Continue on High 13 to 15 minutes or until syrup separates into threads.
Stir in melted butter, baking soda and vanilla just until light and bubbly.
Pour into cookie sheet (Teflon coated). Spread.
Cool for approximately 1 hour and break into pieces. Makes 1 1/4 pounds.

title: garden risotto chicken
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry and cut into 1-inch pieces. Heat canola oil in 12-inch nonstick skillet on medium-high heat. Add onion and garlic. Cook for 2 minutes. Add orzo, broccoli and broth. Reduce heat to medium and cover. Cook for 6 minutes, stirring frequently. Add cut up chicken. Cook for 6 minutes. Mix in corn, salt and pepper. Cook for 5 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in cheese gently. Serve hot. Makes 6 servings.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Fill cupcake papers (with wafers on bottom of each) about 2/3 full with cream mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool.
Top each with cherry pie filling. Chill and serve.

title: no crust coconut pie
directions: Mix sugar and margarine; add flour.
Beat eggs; add milk and vanilla.
Mix all together.
Add coconut and pour into well-greased 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes or until mixture is set and golden brown.

title: 10 minute after school brownies(microwave)
directions: In 8-inch square dish, place butter and cocoa.
Microwave on High 2 minutes until butter is melted.
Stir to blend.
Beat eggs slightly in bowl.
Add sugar, flour and butter mixture and beat at medium speed until blended.
Pour into square dish.
Microwave on High 8 minutes.
Makes about 16 squares.
Perfect for after school and can be done in 15 minutes.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Cut apricots; add to orange juice (let stand 30 minutes). Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream butter, sugar and eggs; beat.
Blend in apricots and juice.
Stir in flour mixture.
Mix until smooth.
Add nuts.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour. This is great in Hawaiian bread!
Water chestnuts can be added.

title: pepperoni bread
directions: Roll bread dough out in a 12 x 15-inch rectangle.
Beat together with fork the egg, oregano and Parmesan cheese.
Brush over dough.
Layer pepperoni and cheese (pepperoni first) over dough.
Roll as for jelly roll, folding in ends and pulling towards you.
Put on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.
Cool and slice.

title: dump cake
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, dump in pie filling; spread evenly.
Dump in pineapple and spread evenly.
Spread evenly the coconut.
Sprinkle the cake mix on and spread evenly.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix, then pour melted butter over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sauerkraut casserole
directions: In a skillet, cook sausage and onion until sausage is brown and onion is tender; drain.
Stir in apples, water, sauerkraut, brown sugar and caraway seed.
Transfer to a 2 1/2 quart baking dish. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Garnish with parsley if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken creole
directions: Coat a large non-stick skillet with cooking spray, place over medium high heat until hot.
Add onion and next 3 ingredients, saute until crisp about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add chicken and next 5 ingredients.
Cook 25 minutes.
Serve over rice, sprinkle with parsley.
Yields 4 servings.

title: corny corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into greased 9-inch pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until browned.

title: simple beef stew
directions: Brown beef in bacon grease.
Chop veggies in large pieces and add to the meat in a large Dutch oven. Add bay leaf and 2 cups water. Cook 1 to 2 hours or until tender.

title: divinity
directions: Combine sugar, syrup, water and salt in heavy saucepan.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook without stirring until candy thermometer registers 260° or a teaspoon of syrup will form a hard ball when dropped in cold water.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Beat boneless chicken (or veal) until 1/4-inch thick.
Put 1 slice of ham and 1 slice of cheese inside and roll chicken up. Dip into egg and roll into crushed corn flakes.
Pin with toothpick.

title: cookie kisses
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees. Slice the dough into 9 - 1 inch thick slices. Cut each slice into quarters. Place 1 dough quarter in each muffins cups sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Press the dough over the bottom and up the side of each muffins cup. Place 1 candy kiss in each prepared muffins cup. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until the edges are light brown. Cool in the muffin cups on a wire rack for 15 minutes. Remove to a wire rack to cool completely.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add milk and slowly add 1 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix well and add dry ingredients slowly.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Beat in 1/2 cup sugar.
Add lemon juice.
Fold into cake batter gently.
Turn into grease tube pan.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour.
Turn pan upside down for 10 minutes and remove pan.

title: banana slush punch
directions: Mix sugar in hot water, let cool.
Add juices.
Blend in bananas and lemon juice.
Freeze in (2) 1 gal. ziploc baggies. Remove from freezer 3 - 4 hours before use.
Mix 1 bag to 1 qt. ginger ale.
Serves 50.

title: clam cakes from rhode island
directions: Mix together dry ingredients.
Add eggs, milk, clam juice, and clams.
Heat oil to 375 degrees and drop batter by the tablespoons into fat.
Fry until brown.
Drain on paper towels. Serve with chowder.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and Crisco together until smooth.
Add milk that has been mixed with the vinegar.
Knead together and separate into 4 balls.
Roll out each ball for 1 crust.
Fill with favorite fruit filling.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, 375° for 50 minutes.
Makes four crusts.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix well.
Pour into a lightly buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sets up quickly.
Refrigerate for easy slicing.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add flour slowly.
Add potato chips and nuts.
Roll into small balls and press down with wet fork.
Bake in a 325° oven on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 15 minutes or until edges are lightly browned.

title: wassail
directions: Using an electric percolator, put apple cider and cranapple juice in the bottom.
Put remaining ingredients in top cup of percolator.
When wassail has perked serve with additional cinnamon sticks in cups, if desired.

title: lord's supper bread
directions: Mix together well the flour, shortening and water.
Roll out 1/8-inch thick and bake until brown.

title: (frozen) strawberry dessert
directions: Mix in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put in oven at 325° for 20 or 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Mash avocados.
Combine tomato, salad dressing, onion, salt and lemon juice; mix well.
Stir in bacon just before serving.

title: pecan or coconut pralines
directions: Put sugar, Karo, milk and water in large saucepan.
Cook over medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Cook to soft ball stage or 230°. Remove from heat, add butter, vanilla, pecans or coconut.
Beat well.
Drop by tablespoons on wax paper, small amounts and work fast.
Let cool.
Store in tightly closed container.

title: pinto bean fudge
directions: Put the confectioners sugar in large bowl, set aside.
In another bowl blend the pinto beans, melted margarine, cocoa and vanilla.
Add cocoa mixture to sugar mixture and mix thoroughly, add nuts if desired.
Pour into greased 8 x 8-inch pan and keep refrigerated.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together the margarine, Crisco, sugar and egg yolks. Stir together the flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture. Add buttermilk and vanilla.
Beat egg whites until stiff; fold in. Add nuts and coconut.
Bake in 3 greased and floured pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Use Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: lemon-lime jello dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water; let cool.
Add ingredients.
Stir until blended.
Pour into dish and put in refrigerator to gel.
Do not mix.

title: baked spinach with sour cream
directions: Cook spinach using package directions.
Drain well.
Combine onion soup mix and sour cream.
Mix well.
Stir sour cream mixture into spinach.
Place in a baking dish.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: pear and ginger beer
directions: Pour pear nectar, ginger beer and lime juice into a pitcher half filled with ice.
Stir to blend.
Pour into tall glasses and garnish with lime slices.

title: creamed chipped beef on toast
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt the butter and saute the onion until clear.
Stir in the flour with a whisk and the hot milk, stirring all the time, until the mixture thickens.
When the mixture is thick, add the remaining ingredients; heat for a moment. Serve over toast.
Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Measure all ingredients into large mixer bowl.
Beat on medium speed 1/2 minute, scraping side and bottom of bowl constantly. Pour into pan.
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan.
Cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: raisin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour in crust.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until set in center.

title: 1-2-3 fudge sauce
directions: Put Carnation, sugar and chocolate in saucepan.
Set saucepan on burner and turn heat to medium.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Arrange dried beef on bottom of greased crock-pot.
Wrap each piece of chicken with strip of bacon and place on top of dried beef.
Mix soup (not diluted), sour cream and flour.
Pour over chicken and cover.
Cook on low heat for 8 to 10 hours or on high for 3 to 5 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: big, fat chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, sugar and vanilla; add eggs and mix until smooth.
Mix milk and yogurt together.
Set aside.
Mix all dry ingredients (except cocoa) together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk/yogurt mixture.
Mix cocoa with hot water to form a paste.
Beat into batter.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes for 2 layers; 45 to 50 minutes for tube pan.
Frost with buttercream frosting.

title: milky way ice cream
directions: Melt Milky Way bars in microwave.
Blend in blender with evaporated milk.
Pour into 1 gallon container.
Combine sugar and eggs; add milk and vanilla.
Add to candy bar mixture in ice cream freezer and freeze as usual.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda and salt together and set aside.
Mix sugar and shortening together, then add eggs, sour milk and bananas.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake in well-greased loaf pan for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.
Let stand for 20 minutes before removing from pan.

title: coney island hot dog sauce
directions: Combine everything except wieners and simmer until thick. Grind wiener and add to sauce.
Stir.
Cook 15 minutes longer. (Do not brown ground beef first.)
If the sauce is a little thin, add a few crumbled soda crackers to the sauce.
Makes 30 servings.

title: onion shortbread
directions: Saute onions in butter.
Mix with sour cream, dill, salt and half the cheese.
Combine corn, milk, muffin mix, egg and hot sauce.
Put muffin mix in buttered 10-inch skillet.
Spread with onion mixture and top with rest of cheese.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Coat pork chops with mixed, dry ingredients.
Brown well in hot oil.
Put chops in crock-pot.
Add soup and cook low for 6 to 8 hours or high for 3 to 4 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: spareribs
directions: In Dutch oven, brown sausages.
Remove and drain off fat.
In same pan, brown ribs, half at a time; remove.
Return meats to pan. Add undrained tomatoes, beef broth, olives and parsley.
Cover and simmer 1 hour or until ribs are tender.
Remove meats; keep warm.
Skim off fat; measure sauce.
Add water, if necessary, to make 2 1/2 cups liquid and return to pan.
Blend flour with 1/2 cup of cold water; stir into liquid.
Cook and stir until bubbly. Serve meat over hot cooked noodles.
Pass sauce.
Makes 6 servings.

title: percolator punch
directions: In basket of percolator, place whole allspice, broken cinnamon sticks, brown sugar, cloves and salt.
In bottom of percolator, place cranberry juice cocktail and pineapple juice.
Add water to the nine cup mark.
Perk as you would coffee.

title: nutty caramel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter a 13 x 9 x 3-inch baking pan. Set aside.
In a large bowl of an electric mixer, beat 1 cup (2 sticks) butter with granulated sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in flour until well mixed.
Pat evenly into prepared pan.
Bake until edges are brown and center looks dry, about 15 minutes.
Remove to a wire rack while preparing topping.
Maintain oven temperature.

title: apricot balls
directions: Blend apricots, coconut and milk.
Let stand about 2 hours to firm.
The nuts may be added to mixture and the balls, rolled in confectioners sugar.
Mixed dried fruit may be used.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: lemon ice cream
directions: Mix well and freeze.

title: walnut butterscotch balls
directions: Put butterscotch pieces into top of a 2-quart double boiler. Place over hot water until bits are melted.
Blend in condensed milk.
Stir in cornflakes, walnuts, raisins and cherries. Spread the finely chopped walnuts on a piece of waxed paper for coating. Shape about a teaspoon of the butterscotch mixture into a small ball.
Roll in nuts to coat.
Place on a cookie sheet or flat pan. Chill until firm.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: bubbat(sausage bread)
directions: Scald milk; cool to lukewarm.
Add dissolved yeast, sugar, egg and salt.
Add flour to make a soft dough.
Let raise until double in size.
Punch dough and divide.
Put one layer of dough in well-greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with sausage (make sure there is plenty of sausage); add another layer of dough.
Let raise 30 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for at least one hour until well browned.
Try this with fruit salad for a fall or winter supper.

title: christmas chocolate candy balls
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine and add condensed milk.
Stir in confectioners sugar, then add the nuts and coconut.
Mix well and make up the balls.
Line cookie sheets with waxed paper and arrange balls on them.
Melt the paraffin on low heat; add chocolate chips and stir constantly.
Dip balls in chocolate and put on waxed paper to set.
Makes about 100 balls.
Sets up real quick.
Put in freezer bags and store until needed.

title: sandwich snacks
directions: Slice rolls lengthwise.
Heat first 2 ingredients and spoon on inside of rolls (2 layers of each is usually enough).
Place top back on rolls.
Heat oven to 350° until cheese melts.
Cut in 2 or 3 roll size. These can be frozen before heating to serve later.

title: shrimp spread
directions: Mix all together and pour into mold.
Serve with crackers.

title: tropical bars
directions: In medium saucepan combine juice and enough water to equal 1 cup.
Sprinkle gelatine over and let stand 1 minute.
Heat and stir over low heat until gelatine is completely dissolved.
Stir in honey and then remaining ingredients.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch baking pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut into bars to serve.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: incredible coconut pie(1940)
directions: Combine flour, sugar, eggs, milk, butter and vanilla.
Mix well and stir in coconut.
Pour into a deep baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and milk until light and fluffy.
Add peanut butter and beat until smooth.
Fold Cool Whip into peanut butter mixture and pour into pie shells.
Chill for 4 to 6 hours or overnight.
This pie freezes well and will last 2 to 3 months.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix together in pan sugar, margarine, milk and cocoa.
Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add creamy peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
Spoon on wax paper and put in refrigerator.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and egg.
Add dry ingredients to mixture.
Add milk and stir.
Gently fold in blueberries. Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, shortening and sugar in large bowl.
Mix yeast in 1 cup warm water.
Let yeast dissolve about 5 minutes, then mix all together.
Leave in bowl and set on top of oven; cover.
Let rise for 1 hour.
Roll out on floured board; cut like biscuits.
Dip in butter.
Place in pan; let set 30 minutes more and bake.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Stir together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Beat shortening and 1 1/2 cups sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Add dry ingredients, beating until well combined.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Roll into a mixture of 3 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Place balls on cookie sheet and bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: alaskan baked halibut
directions: Melt butter or oleo in bottom of oven proof dish.
Lay fish on top.
Cover the top of fish with the rest of the ingredients that have been mixed together.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
If not browned, stick under broiler for a few minutes.

title: tuna braid
directions: Make bread dough 2 hours or more ahead.
Thaw and drain spinach (Swiss chard also works well).
Chop spinach and set aside. Combine tuna, cottage cheese, spinach and cheeses.

title: ham and asparagus rolls
directions: Roll 2 stalks of cooked asparagus in each ham slice.
Melt butter, blending in flour, salt and pepper, adding milk slowly; cook until smooth and thick.
Add cheese and stir until melted and blended.
Pour sauce over ham rolls.
Bake at 350° until hot and slightly browned, 20 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: refritos from mexico
directions: Peel and chop the onion and garlic.
Melt the margarine in a pan over a medium heat and fry the onion and garlic gently for 5 minutes.
Mash the beans and add to the mixture with the pepper. Cook it all through until hot.

title: frozen orange dessert
directions: Combine first three ingredients; set aside 3/4 cup.
Press remaining crumb mixture into ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Set side.

title: tipsy roast beef
directions: Place
roast in crock-pot.
Sprinkle the onion soup mix over it.
Pour
in the beer and cook for several hours on low. Test for
doneness.
(Very good gravy.) If gravy is too rich, add a little water.

title: country chicken and biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cook mixed vegetables, onion and celery in broth in 5-quart Dutch oven until tender.
Heat to boiling. Stir cornstarch into cold water until dissolved; stir into broth. Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir constantly for one minute.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chicken and parsley. Pour into ungreased rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Shape into small balls the size of a walnut.
Deep fry in a wok or skillet until well browned. Drain.
Arrange in a loaf pan or casserole.
Pour spaghetti sauce over and bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 350° oven. May be topped with cheese before baking.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple pie cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; stir in eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt. Stir half of flour mixture into shortening mixture.
Beat in 2 tablespoons of the hot water.
Stir in remaining flour mixture, then the remaining water, beating after each addition.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Spread in two greased 9 x 9-inch pans or 1 greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes or until sides pull away from pans.
Excellent with vanilla ice cream.

title: old fashioned cookies
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients. Roll out about 1/4 inch thick.
Cut out with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° about 10 minutes.

title: cherry torte
directions: Mix flour, 1/2 cup powdered sugar, graham crackers and butter together.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes; cool completely.

title: homemade vanilla extract
directions: In a 3-cup glass container with a tight fitting lid, combine vanilla beans with the vodka.
Cap and allow to "steep" at room temperature for 3 weeks.
Remove vanilla beans and strain liquid through a cheesecloth, if necessary.
In a medium saucepan, combine water and sugar, stirring constantly, until it comes to a boil and sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and cool.
Stir into vodka that has been strained.
Pour mixture into a bottle; cap and allow to sit at room temperature for one month.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt together the margarine and peanut butter.
Add graham cracker crumbs, coconut and sugar.
Mix well and roll into small balls.
Melt paraffin and chips in a double boiler.
Dip candy and place on wax paper.
Makes about 100 candy balls.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken and pull meat from the bones.
Heat cream of chicken soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes together until smooth and creamy. In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the bottom with crushed Doritos, then half of the chicken.
Add half of the chopped onion, soup mixture and sprinkle half of the Cheddar cheese.
Repeat the layers again and add more chips on top.

title: unbaked oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix together and bring to boil first 3 ingredients.
Boil for 1 minute.
After boiling remove from heat.
Mix in oats, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Melt 4 Tbsp. butter in a large pot.
Add salt and flour.
Add milk slowly.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Add sliced potatoes. Bring to a boil.
Put potatoes in a 13 inch x 9 inch x 2 inch baking dish and dot with remaining butter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken fajitas
directions: Prepare salad dressing according to package directions.
Add soy sauce, lemon juice, Worcestershire, garlic, salt and pepper. Marinate chicken overnight or several hours.
Broil or grill chicken until done.
Wrap onion, bell pepper, tomato, mushrooms and chicken in flour tortillas.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Combine dry ingredients and work in shortening.
Stir in yeast and buttermilk.
Dough will seem too soft to handle.
Handle with well floured hands.
Roll or shape as you like. Bake in hot 400° oven for 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: southern fried rice
directions: Slice potatoes, carrots, onion, bell pepper and hot dogs. Brown (fry) over medium heat.
Beat eggs and pour over fried mixture.
Mix until eggs are cooked.
Cook rice according to box directions.
Combine fried mixture with rice and stir well. Season to taste.
Serve hot.

title: harwood jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into hot greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: pizzakeen(easter meat pie)
directions: Use 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, ungreased.
(Optional:
Line pan with pie crust.)

title: bran muffin mix(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Mix water, buttermilk and soda well and set aside.
Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and salt.
Mix these 2 mixtures together in large bowl.
Then add the brans and flour.
Mix well.
Store in refrigerator.
Can be kept up to 4 weeks, taking out amounts as needed.
Bake at 375°.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: eggplant cheese bake
directions: Remove stalks from eggplant and cut lengthwise in 1/2-inch thick slices.
Sprinkle with salt.
Leave for 1 hour, then rinse and pat dry.
Coat with flour.
Preheat the oven to 350°.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Do not mix cake mix according to directions on box.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mash avocado with fork, add lemon juice, salt, chili powder and garlic; mix well.

title: pork egg rolls
directions: Beat egg whites with water to make egg wash.
Cook Ramen noodles (set aside spice packet).
Drain.
Put into large bowl. Add raw cabbage, celery and onion.
Add ginger and set aside.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup and water until it spins a thread. Add peanuts and stir continuously, cooking until it turns a brownish gold. Remove from heat, add butter, salt and soda.
Stir until butter is melted, pour into buttered pan.

title: sausage bean chowder
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Pour off grease.
In a large kettle combine all ingredients except potatoes and green peppers. Simmer covered for 1 hour or longer.
Add potatoes and green peppers. Cook until potatoes are tender - 30 to 45 minutes.

title: green punch
directions: Dissolve
gelatin
in hot water.
Add sugar, then lemon juice, pineapple juice and water.
Mix and pour over sherbet. Makes 2 gallons or 64 four ounce servings.

title: rice and shrimp salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, then marinate with oil, vinegar, salt, curry and onions.
Add peas, celery and shrimp and then mix with mayonnaise.

title: edible aquarium
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups ice and water.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened; remove and pour fish in Jell-O, slightly thickened; put in refrigerator until set. Serves 4.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder and salt.
Put in the shortening with fingers.
Add milk gradually; mix to a smooth dough.
Turn onto floured board.
Divide into 6 portions and roll out enough to cover an apple.
Place an apple on each piece of dough.
Fill the space from which the core was taken with sugar and a little cinnamon.
Wet the edges of the dough; fold them over the apple.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
(Dumplings may be steamed instead of baked.)

title: oreo cookie dessert(dirt cake)
directions: Mix sugar, butter, cream cheese and Cool Whip in one bowl. In another bowl, combine pudding mixes with milk. Combine mixtures; pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle crushed Oreos on top. Chill.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Put tomatoes and sauce in saucepan, adding chopped pepper and finely chopped parsley.
Add crushed garlic cloves, 1/3 fennel.
Sweeten with sugar (approximately 2 tablespoons, according to taste).
Add basil.
Simmer, uncovered, for one hour. Stir frequently.
Add sugar at last of cooking time.
Taste for possibly more basil or sugar.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cream together 1/2 cup sugar and butter.
Add baking powder, flour, milk and salt.
Line 8 x 8-inch pan with grease and add fruit.
Spread dough on top of fruit.
Add 1 cup sugar over top of dough.
Then pour 1/2 cup water over all.
Bake at 350° for 34 to 40 minutes.

title: fresh cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food processor with water, then drain. Put sugar with ground cranberries and soak overnight.
Remove core from apple and cut up with a knife.
Chop up orange, minus the white pith if possible.
When making up the jello, use less water if some water was used in the chopping.
Mix all ingredients and let set.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Mix together last 3 ingredients.
Arrange chicken, bone side down in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Uncover and bake 10 minutes more.

title: date bars
directions: Add 1/2 cup nuts and spread on crumb mixture; spread the rest of crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for about 1/2 hour.

title: glorified cabbage
directions: Chop cabbage fine and boil until very tender in salted water; drain. Wilt onion in oleo. When wilted, add cheese in hunks and allow to melt over low heat.
When melted, add soup.
Blend. Add cabbage and mix well.
Add about 1/2 cup bread crumbs and parsley. Season to taste.
Put in greased 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole. Sprinkle bread crumbs on top and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Serves about 8.

title: quick chocolate fondue
directions: In a small bowl, combine chocolate chips and milk.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Stir until smooth.
Dip apple sections, banana chunks, strawberries or favorite fresh fruit.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar, vanilla and 1 egg.
Mix well.
Spread onto bottom of pastry shell. Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Carefully pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: foil dinner on grill
directions: On large piece of foil, put potatoes, carrots, onions and pieces of ground beef; salt and pepper (garlic) to taste.
Put dots of butter on top.
Fold foil like a packet, sealing ends well.
Cook on grill 20 minutes each side or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 5 or 6 packets.

title: chili-con-queso
directions: *Adjust amount of green chili to your preference.

title: green dessert jello
directions: Mash jello and let set until soft.
Mix whipped whipping cream, cottage cheese and pineapple in jello.
Let set until jelled.

title: waffles
directions: Beat eggs until light and fluffy.
Then mix in other ingredients.
Bake in waffle iron till golden brown.
Tastes great with homemade pudding.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cook both tapioca pudding mixes using juice drained off pineapple and oranges, adding enough orange juice to equal 4 cups. Let cool.
Add fruit to pudding and refrigerate.

title: microwave  banana  muffins
directions: Mix ingredients all together.
Place 2 thicknesses of paper cup liners in microwavable pan (for 6 muffins); divide mixture evenly into 6 cups.
Microwave on high, turning 1/4 turn every 30 seconds for 2 1/2 to 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar, if desired.

title: aunt syl's bake fish fillet
directions: Dredge the fish in the dry milk and Parmesan cheese mixture. Put the tomato sauce in a shallow baking dish.
Add the fish. Sprinkle the fish with the remaining cheese mixture.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes or until golden brown or microwave for 4 to 6 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni.
Mix rest of ingredients.
Add to hot, drained macaroni.
Bake at 350° about 25 minutes.

title: western beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion, celery and green pepper. Cook until meat is brown. Drain fat. Add noodles, salt, pepper, ketchup, soup and water.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, cheese, eggs and peanut butter together.
Mix in 1 Cool Whip; put in crust.
Top with the other container of Cool Whip; keep in refrigerator or you can freeze.

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In saucepan over low heat, melt chips with sweetened condensed milk and salt.
Remove from heat, stir in walnuts and vanilla, spread into aluminum foil-lined 8 or 9 in square pan-chill 2 hr until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board, peel off foil and cut into
squares.

title: quick apple roll
directions: Use a 2-quart baking dish; grease.
Add all ingredients into dish.
Mix well.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: raisin carrot muffins
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and ginger. Stir in carrots, raisins and nuts separately.
Combine undrained pineapple, eggs, margarine and vanilla. Stir into dry ingredients until just blended.
Spoon into greased muffin tin (or paper). Bake in 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool on rack.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: quick and easy tamale chicken
directions: Spread tomato soup in 11 x 7-inch baking dish.
Slice tamales in 1/2-inch rounds.
Place on top of soup.
Place chicken breasts on top of tamales.
Spread white sauce over chicken breasts. Drizzle tamale sauce that is left over in can, over all.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: salad and dressing(from the 55 restaurants)
directions: Combine oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and garlic powder (or pressed garlic) and shake well.
Store in refrigerator.

title: creamed salmon
directions: Place butter in a 2-quart ovenware measure.
Cook butter 30 seconds or until butter is melted.
Add flour and seasonings. Blend to a smooth paste.
Add milk gradually, stirring constantly. Continue cooking about 6 minutes to thicken.
Chop 1 1/2 hard-cooked eggs, reserving the other 1/2 egg for garnish.
Add egg to white sauce.
Mix well.
Combine white sauce and salmon in a 1-quart ovenware casserole.
Cover.
Continue cooking 3 to 4 minutes.
Serve over hot toast or biscuits.
Garnish with sliced, hard-cooked egg and parsley.

title: leftover ham casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Cook noodles
and drain.
Combine soup and milk in saucepan until smooth.
Add onion, mustard and sour cream; stir.
Add hot noodles and ham.
Toss with a fork.
Put in the baking dish and top with mixed butter and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle the top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 25 to 35 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: spicy punch
directions: Heat the cranberry juice with cloves and cinnamon slowly about 10 minutes.
Remove cloves and cinnamon and then add juices. Serve either hot or cold.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar, Milnot and water together and cook on medium heat until soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and corn syrup.
Beat until creamy and stiff.
Spread on buttered place.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Salt, pepper and garlic salt chicken, brown lightly, transfer to ovenproof dish.
Smother with other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, uncovered.
Cover chicken and bake for 20 minutes longer.
This is real good with rice, just spoon sauce over chicken and rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add the beaten eggs; mix well.
Add the mashed bananas, flour, soda, nuts and vanilla. Pour into a well-greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until brown and firm in its center.
Let cool 1/2 hour before trying to remove from the pan.

title: grilled center-cut ham
directions: Brush ham with steak sauce and place on charcoal grill.
Cook for 20 minutes, turning every 5 minutes.
Add steak sauce each time you turn it.

title: double easy cheezy spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, green pepper and garlic.
Add soups (tomato and mushroom) and water and let simmer for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Add cheese, salt and pepper and stir until cheese melts.
Cook spaghetti and drain well, then add to meat mixture.
Put into greased casserole dish topped with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until very hot and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: boiled custard
directions: Break eggs into large bowl; add salt and 1 cup milk.
Beat with rotary beater, adding sugar gradually until well blended.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Beat eggs well.
Add rest of ingredients and beat well. Pour into greased
and
floured	cookie	sheet.	Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Frost while still slightly warm.

title: lime-lemon delight cake
directions: Combine cake mix, jello, water, oil, eggs and salt in large bowl of mixer.
Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 minutes.
When baked, remove from oven.
Punch holes in cake while still hot, about one-inch deep and one-inch apart.
Do not go to bottom of pan with holes.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat and top with 3 slices of cheese.

title: special k bars
directions: Combine peanut butter, syrup and brown sugar in a saucepan. Stir over medium heat until heated.
Pour over Special K and stir.
Press into a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and butterscotch chips together.
Pour over bars.
Cut in squares.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high speed for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Spread in a well sprayed sheet pan (12 x 17 x 1-inch).
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes, or until toothpick comes out clean.
Loosen edges carefully from pan and dump cake on towel, well sprinkled with powdered sugar. While cake is still hot, roll cake in towel from narrow side. Cool on wire rack.
Unroll cooled cake to put filling and nuts on.

title: peanut butter and jelly toast
directions: Toast your slices of bread.
While still warm, spread with peanut butter, and top with jelly.
The warm bread makes the peanut butter very soft.

title: fast supper
directions: Save the broth from your roast chicken, beef or pork.
Place in refrigerator; all the fat will rise and you can remove it.
Heat broth and add a little water and flour.
Add meat or meatballs. Heat thoroughly; serve over rice, noodles or potatoes.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and onion soup mix.
Mix in the rest of the ingredients, except macaroni, and cook on medium for 45 minutes. The last 10 minutes of cooking, you can add macaroni.

title: dorothy's white cake
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 cup coconut and 1/2 teaspoon almond extract; bake.
While still warm, pour La Creme coconut over.
Cool.
Then add Cool Whip, 1/2 cup coconut and 1/2 teaspoon almond.

title: deep dish chicago pizza
directions: About 1 hour before serving:
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat, heat sausages and 1/4 cup water to boiling.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Remove cover; continue cooking, turning sausages frequently until sausages are well browned, about 20 minutes. Drain on paper towels.
Cut sausages into 1/4-inch thick slices. Place in bowl.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Prepare hot roll mix as label directs, but use 1 cup water and omit egg.
Do not let dough rise.
Pat dough halfway up sides of dish.
In medium bowl mix sauce, parsley, sugar, basil, oregano and pepper plus sausage.
Sprinkle half of Mozzarella cheese over dough.
Top with sauce mixture, then Parmesan cheese, then remaining Mozzarella.
Bake on bottom rack of oven 25 minutes or until top is hot and bubbly and crust is brown and crisp.

title: sweet french dressing
directions: Combine together and shake well.
Let stand all day and night in refrigerator.

title: party time fruit punch
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together in a large punch bowl. When ready to serve, add a block of ice to the bowl.
Serves 20.

title: quick broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in butter in skillet.
Add rice, Cheez Whiz, milk and soup, stirring constantly until Cheez Whiz is melted.
Thaw broccoli, place in casserole dish.
Spoon sauce over broccoli.
Bake at 325°
for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: mustard-sauced vegetables au gratin
directions: Cook broccoli, cauliflower and carrots until crisp-tender. Drain well. Cut red pepper into thin strips. Cook celery and onion in 3 tablespoons butter until tender. Blend in flour, mustard, basil, bouillon and 1/4 teaspoon pepper. Add milk. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Stir in vegetables. Turn into a 10 x 6 1/2 x 2-inch baking dish. (This can be covered and chilled up to 24 hours.)

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour and soda together.
Mix well the softened butter and sugars.
Add vanilla and eggs, beating well.
Add flour to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cocoa crunchies
directions: Mix together sugar, cocoa, milk and margarine.
Bring to a boil and boil hard for 1 minute (no more). Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well and drop on waxed paper with teaspoon. Refrigerate.
Serve when cold.

title: refrigerator cheese cake
directions: Blend butter, 1/4 cup sugar, crumbs and cinnamon.
Line spring-form pan with 3/4 of mixture.
Soften gelatin in 1/2 cup water.
Cook egg yolks, remaining sugar and water in double boiler until thickened.
Add gelatin.
Beat into cheese with lemon juice, rind and salt.
Chill; beat well.
Fold in cream with stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour onto crumbs.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill until firm.
Serves 12.

title: kolacky (polish cookies)
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese. Mix and add sifted dry ingredients and work into butter and cream cheese. Roll dough on floured board to 1/4-inch thick and use round cookie cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Make small indentation with thumb in middle of cookie and put 1/2 teaspoon of filling of your choice. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Let cool.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Mix soda with flour. Mix with other ingredients and bake approximately 1 hour and 15 minutes in ring mold at 350°.

title: best ever chile
directions: In Dutch oven, cook beef, onion and celery until meat is brown and vegetables are tender. Add beans and remaining ingredients.
Cover; simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken sauterne
directions: Season chicken and brown in butter slowly. Remove chicken; add onion and cook until clear. Put chicken in dish and mix other ingredients. Pour over chicken. Let stand in fridge overnight. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Gravy is delicious served over rice.

title: mother's pecan pie
directions: Melt butter, mix all ingredients and put in pie shell.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: campbelled eggs
directions: In a bowl, stir soup until smooth.
Gradually stir in eggs. In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter over low heat.
Pour egg mixture into skillet.
As mixture begins to set around the edges, lift cooked portion with a spatula so uncooked portion can flow to bottom of the pan.
Continue lifting until eggs are completely set, about 8 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: milk chocolate bar cake
directions: Prepare cake batter according to package directions. Pour into 3 greased and floured 8-inch round cake pans. Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes. Remove from pans. Cool completely on wire racks.

title: tennessee pumpkin bread
directions: Grease regular loaf pan.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cream the shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Stir in pumpkin.
Add nuts.
Blend in dry ingredients in 4 additions.
Alternate with water until smooth. Turn batter in prepared pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.

title: frozen praline pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine.
Add egg and mix well.
Press into bottom and up the sides of ungreased 8-inch pie pan.
Poke a few small holes in crust to prevent air pockets from forming under crust.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: bread
directions: Mix in order given, adding flour as needed to make dough easy to knead.
Knead 10 minutes.
Let rise once to make rolls.
Let rise twice before making into loaves.
Rolls, bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Loaves, bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chicken tenders
directions: Slice the Chicken Breast into tender-size strips; set aside. Add Water to the beaten Eggs.
Cover a plate with Bread Crumbs and another plate with Flour.

Take Chicken strips and dredge in Flour, roll into egg mixture and finally roll in the Bread Crumbs. Depending on preferred way to fry, place coated chicken tenders in the oil and fry for approximately 5 minutes.
I prefer deep frying because it leaves less fat on the tenders and they are cooked when the float on top of oil.

title: freezer corn
directions: Stir together corn, half and half and butter.
Put in roaster in 325° oven for 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Cool.
Freezer in containers.
Your choice of size.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together, roll into balls and place onto cookie sheet. Flatten out with the bottom of a sugared glass.
Bake at 325° for about 8 to 10 minutes. Watch closely, they cook pretty fast, mainly judge by bottom edges of cookies.
They are almost too easy and contain no flour.

title: squash pie(dessert)
directions: Beat eggs, flour and sugar together.
Add butter and extracts. Fold in squash.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell.
Bake for 50 minutes in preheated 350° oven.

title: rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 3/4 cup warm water. Add sugar. Scald milk; add shortening. Cool to lukewarm.
Add to yeast; add flour. Turn onto floured board; knead until elastic.
Place in greased bowl; turn over. Rise until double; punch down.
Make into rolls. Place in greased pan. Lightly oil top; let rise. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes until brown.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Combine sugars, pumpkin, oil and eggs.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture and mix well.
Stir in nuts and water.
Pour into a well-greased loaf pan (9 x 5 x 3-inches).
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: fig bars
directions: Mix oleo, sugar and eggs.
Stir in vanilla.
Blend flour, soda and salt together and stir into mixture.
Chill dough.
Divide dough in half and roll out on floured wax paper.
Blend figs in blender then spread on rolled dough.
Roll out rest of dough and place on top of figs.
Seal edges.
Bake at 400° for about 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut bars to desired size.
To make a full cookie sheet, double recipe.

title: marinara sauce(makes about 3 cups)
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, in oil, cook garlic and onion until tender, 5 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, their liquid and remaining ingredients.
Reduce heat to low, cover and cook 20 minutes until thickened, stirring occasionally.
(I cook my sauce several hours and add a little water; however, it is still delicious when cooked for the 20 minutes or so.)

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 300°.
Prepare crust.
In mixed bowl, beat cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth, then eggs and vanilla.
Toss 1/2 cup chips with flour.
Add to cheese mixture.
Pour into pan.
Sprinkle remaining chips over top.
Bake 1 hour or until center is set.
Cool.
Chill (refrigerate).

title: pan broiled pork chops with apple barbecue sauce
directions: In small saucepan, mix well juice, catsup, sugar, salt, cloves, ginger, garlic and green onion.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, stirring occasionally.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Dip chops in sauce; place in shallow baking dish.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
If time permits, bring chops to room temperature before cooking.
In large skillet, heat oil.
Add chops; cook, turning once, 8 to 10 minutes or until tender and no longer pink inside.
Serve with reheated leftover sauce.
Makes 4 servings.

title: grace stocker's chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Set aside.
In another bowl, beat margarine and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, orange peel and zucchini.
Alternately stir in dry ingredients and milk.
Add nuts last.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diana's chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and green pepper.
Drain off fat. Add tomatoes, tomato sauce and spices.
Simmer approximately 45 minutes.
Add beans and simmer another 15 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: In a 2 1/2-quart pan, combine first 5 ingredients.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil rapidly to hard ball stage (250°).
Remove from heat, stir in soda quickly.
Stir thoroughly and pour over popcorn.
Stir gently until all kernels are coated. Bake for 1 hour, stirring 2 or 3 times while in the oven.
Turn out onto waxed paper, spread apart and cool.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 6 quarts.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly by hand.
Drop by teaspoon into sifted powdered sugar.
Roll and place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: microwave chocolate pie
directions: Combine marshmallows, chocolate morsels, milk and unsweetened chocolate in a 2-quart glass mixing bowl.
Microwave at High 4 to 5 minutes, stirring once.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream and pour into prepared Chocolate Crust.
Freeze until firm.
Yields one 9-inch pie.

title: chopped beef dip
directions: Mix all together.
Serve with crackers or veggies.

title: blackberry jam cake
directions: In a medium size bowl mix
the flour, cloves, nutmeg and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Mix the baking soda in the buttermilk.
In a large mixing bowl cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add vanilla, mix well.
To the cream mixture add the jam, flour and buttermilk alternately.
Bake in 3 greased and floured
cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese sharp delights
directions: Combine cheese and butter; cream until well blended.
Sift flour, salt and pepper together; blend into butter mixture. Shape into rolls, 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in waxed paper; refrigerate overnight.
Slice 1/4-inch thick; place on baking sheet.
Bake in preheated 425° oven until edges are lightly browned.

title: broiled chicken cordon bleu
directions: Preheat broiler.
Meanwhile, place poultry on the unheated rack of the broiler pan.
Brush with half of the margarine. Broil 4 inches from the heat for 4 minutes.
Turn poultry over and brush with remaining margarine.
Broil for 4 to 5 minutes more or until tender.
Meanwhile, cut cheese slices in half.
Brush tops of poultry with mustard.
Place one half slice of cheese on top of each piece of poultry, then top with the ham or bacon (if necessary, cut ham slice to fit poultry).
Broil about 30 seconds or until ham is warm.
Then top with remaining cheese.
Broil for 1/2 to 1 minute more or until cheese is melted.
To serve, transfer to dinner plates.
Sprinkle with paprika.
If desired garnish with tomatoes and parsley.
Makes 2 servings.

title: banana boats
directions: Drain the pineapple juice and set juice aside.
Peel and cut the bananas into quarters.
Coat the banana slices in pineapple juice.
Place slices on serving plate.
Make masts and sails by placing grapes and pineapple chunks on toothpicks and stick them into each banana boat. Add crew members (raisins) by attaching with peanut butter.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat eggs and oil until fluffy; add sugar.
Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Add sliced apples and nuts.

title: jello cake
directions: Prepare cake following directions on package.
Pour into a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Dissolve gelatin as directed on package.
With a fork, punch holes in cake all over top.
Pour warm gelatin over cake, down into holes.

title: strawberry fruit parfait
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Chill until partially set. Beat in ice cream with beater.
Fold in berries.
Chill.
Garnish with whole strawberries.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lasagne
directions: Cook package of noodles in water in a large kettle with a tablespoon of salad oil and salt.
Do not cook it completely done. Drain and cool.
Beat eggs until creamy; mix in cottage cheese. Cook hamburger; add spaghetti sauce.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Put 1/4 of meat sauce on bottom.
Put in layer of noodles.
Add 1/3 egg and cottage cheese mixture.
Add layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers 2 more times.
End with meat sauce on top. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Salt and pepper meat; brown on all sides under broiler or in frying pan on stove.
I use a crock-pot now and after browning the meat, add all ingredients and cook all day.
It can be baked in oven at 350° for 30 minutes per 1 pound also.
Cool after cooking. Slice very thin and return to juices.

title: rum balls
directions: Combine crumbs, confectioners sugar, 1 cup of the pecans and cocoa.
Add corn syrup and rum.
Mix well.
Shape into balls. Roll half in sugar and half in nuts.
Yield: 2 dozen.

title: french cream filling]
directions: Mix sugar, flour, cornstarch and salt.
Beat egg yolk slightly and combine with 1/2 cup cold milk.
Add to dry ingredients, forming a smooth paste.
Add warm milk slowly and cook until thick and smooth.
Stir constantly.
Cook 5 minutes after it thickens. Now add oleo; when cool, add vanilla.
Store in refrigerator for 2 hours before filling eclairs.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix together and put into 3-quart flat casserole dish.
Top with crushed cornflakes; sprinkle with butter (1/4 cup).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 16.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
(Don't cut back on butter if you want batter crusty.)
Mix all the above ingredients together (except peaches).
Mixture will be thin.
Place peaches on top.
Pour into pan and bake at 350° for about 35 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions; drain. Combine all ingredients in crock pot and simmer for 30 - 45 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Clean and slice squash.
Cover with water; cook until tender. Drain well. Return to pan; mash well.
Add margarine, eggs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Mash and blend well.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for about 25 to 30 minutes or until top is lightly brown.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Put margarine, oil, cocoa and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Sift flour and sugar together; Pour chocolate mixture over dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Pour into greased 10 X 15 jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
While cake is hot, frost with frosting.

title: white cake
directions: Mix it all together and pour in pan.
Bake in 350° oven until done.

title: peanut sauce for sirloin tips or veal
directions: Grind
the
nuts
and parsley and set aside.
Saute the meat in	oil
until browned on all sides.
Add garlic, onion, tomatoes and
sugar.
Cook
until
liquid has evaporated from tomatoes. Discard garlic.
Add nuts and parsley.
Add nutmeg, thyme
and oregano
and
brown.
Add
stock,
wine,
salt and pepper.	Cook very slowly adding more wine or water if necessary	until
meat is	very
tender.
It
should take about 30 minutes and the sauce should be very thick.

title: crock-pot taco dip
directions: Scramble ground beef and sausage until done (make sure texture is crumbly).
Drain grease from meat.
Add taco seasoning.
Mix and stir well.
Set aside.
Cube Velveeta cheese and place in crock-pot on high.
When cheese is melted, stir in meat mixture. Add picante sauce and stir well.
Turn heat to low.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and add a little sugar and dash of salt. Then add Miracle Whip to your liking.
I use Miracle Whip instead of mayonnaise because it gives it the tartness I prefer.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix together all ingredients except tomato juice.
Roll into balls and roll in flour.
Brown in small amount of shortening. Add 1 cup hot water.
Boil down low and then add tomato juice. Simmer with lid on until thick, about 30 or 40 minutes.
Serve with red beans, rice and cornbread.

title: ground beef or turkey soup
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain.
Stir meat, onion and remaining ingredients together in large pot.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 15 minutes, or until noodles are tender.
Makes 8 servings (1 cup each).

title: soft pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add salt and sugar.
Line cookie sheet with foil (shiny side up).
Blend in flour.
Sprinkle flour on counter and knead dough.
Cut into small pieces and roll into an 18-inch rope.
Shape into pretzels and place on cookie sheet.
Brush with egg and sprinkle with salt. Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: finger jello (knox blox)(day care treats)
directions: In large bowl, mix Knox unflavored gelatine with Jell-O.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatine is completely dissolved. Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.
To serve, cut into 1-inch squares.
Need not be refrigerated.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except corn flake crumbs, and pour in baking dish.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry-cheese salad
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in cranberry juice and cold water.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Shape cream cheese into 18 balls; roll in nuts.
Mix strawberries and sugar.
Pour 1/3 cup thickened gelatin into 6-cup ring mold.
Arrange cheese balls evenly in gelatin mold.
Spoon strawberries over cheese balls.
Carefully pour remaining gelatin over strawberries.
Refrigerate until firm; unmold.
Makes 6 servings.
Contains 190 calories per serving.

title: easy as 1-2-3 mexican salad
directions: Cook rice.
Warm the chili.
Melt Velveeta cheese with the milk.
Layer Fritos, rice, chili, lettuce and onions. Top with melted Velveeta.

title: special yellow cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients.
Sift flour and baking powder. Add alternately with milk and lemon or vanilla.
Beat egg whites and fold in batter.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.
Makes one 8 or 9-inch cake.

title: dixie frankfurter casserole
directions: Brown onion and franks with oil in skillet.
Add tomatoes and simmer.
In small bowl, mix flour, salt, pepper, chili powder and thyme.
Add water and blend well.
Stir in tomato mixture.
Simmer until thickened.
Turn into 2-quart casserole dish; top with corn bread already mixed according to package directions.
Spoon on top.
Bake at 400° for 35 minutes.

title: lemon buttered new potatoes
directions: In a small saucepan, melt butter; add remaining ingredients, except potatoes.
Heat thoroughly.
Place hot potatoes in serving dish; pour butter mixture over potatoes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.
(Put in cracked ice if preferred.)

title: turkish meatballs(kofte)
directions: Mix well ground beef, bread crumbs, onion, egg, black pepper and salt.
Shape into 1-inch balls and flatten slightly.
Fry both sides in hot oil.
Serve warm or cold with French fried potatoes or rice.
Great as a meal or an hors d'oeuvre.

title: pecan brittle
directions: In a large pan add sugar, corn syrup and water. Cook until mixture forms hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Add to syrup mixture the pecans and butter.
Cook until butter browns. Add soda. Pour into buttered pan. While hot, spread thin. When cool, break into pieces.

title: catfish jambalaya
directions: Melt butter in heavy saucepan.
Add onion, pepper, garlic, cilantro and sausage.
Saute until vegetables are tender.
Add bouillon, bay leaf and water.
Bring to boil and simmer 20 minutes.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Store in tightly covered container. Place 2 rounded tablespoons in a mug.
Add boiling water and stir.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Can use a 9 x 13-inch pan or a tube pan (greased and floured). Raisins and coconut may be added to cake, if desired.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: baked crab
directions: Saute pepper, celery and onion in butter.
In a bowl, mix cracker crumbs, cream, salt and pepper to taste and garlic salt. Add sauteed vegetables and crab meat.
Fill crab shells and top each with paprika, parsley and a squeeze of lemon juice.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Or you can put into casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: chocolate crazy cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients into ungreased oblong pan.
Using a spoon, make 3 holes (large, medium and small) in the dry ingredients being sure the bottom of each hole has flour covering.
Put the oil in the large hole, vinegar in the medium hole and vanilla in the small one.
Combine this until crumbly.
Pour cold water over entire mixture and mix with a fork until smooth, but do not beat.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
When cool, frost with your favorite chocolate icing.

title: quick light rolls
directions: Scald the milk; stir in sugar, salt and margarine.
Cool to lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Cool to lukewarm and combine.
Add egg and 2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour until it makes a soft dough.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (free from draft) until doubled in size, about 30 minutes.
Punch down, turn on lightly floured board and shape into rolls.
Let rise in a warm place free from draft until double in size, about 30 minutes.
Bake in preheated hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes.
Yields 24 rolls.

title: cheddar burger skillet
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain fat.
Add soups and drained potatoes.
Heat and serve.

title: jan hagel cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients, except egg white and nutmeats.

title: crispy cookies
directions: Mix together margarine, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add all other dry ingredients slowly.
Mix well.
Then add chocolate chips and nuts, if desired.
Form into small balls.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Yields 5 dozen.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain liquid from cherries and pineapple, and bring to a boil. Add cherry Jello, let this cool, then add Coke and cream cheese. Cream together cheese and add to pineapple and cherries that have been cut in half.
Add nuts if desired.
Combine the two mixtures and when the purple foam has settled, put in the refrigerator to congeal.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into tube pan (greased and floured) for 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: In bowl chop lettuce, green onions and celery.
Place peas, meat and cheese on top.
Spread mayonnaise over top and sprinkle with sugar.
Refrigerate for 24 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: teriyaki marinade
directions: Mix all together and cover meat (beef or chicken). Refrigerate
and marinate for 4 to 6 hours, no longer than 8 hours.

title: chocolate ice cream cake
directions: Bake cake mix using box directions in a loaf pan.
Slice cooked cake in half, vertically.
Take frozen ice cream out of box.
Make sure ice cream keeps box shape.
Slice ice cream vertically equaling size of cake.
Place ice cream on one layer of cake. Place other layer of cake on top of ice cream.
Spread Cool Whip and chocolate syrup over cake.
Top with cherries.

title: peas 'n' peanuts
directions: Mix together sour cream, Worcestershire sauce, garlic salt and lemon juice.
Add peas and peanuts.

title: fluff orange mold
directions: Take liquid from oranges.
Add water to make 1 cup.
Dissolve gelatin in 2 cups hot water.
Stir in liquid from orange sections (1 cup).
Chill in refrigerator until slightly thickened.
Beat until foamy; add the 1 pint sherbet.
Beat until well blended. Fold in orange sections.
Pour into 2-quart mold and chill.

title: hot wiener dip
directions: Mix all ingredients. Add salt and pepper to taste. Marinate in refrigerator overnight. Serve on Ritz crackers.

title: sticky buns
directions: Grease Bundt pan.
Combine butterscotch instant pudding mix and brown sugar in a bowl.
Melt margarine or butter in a bowl. Use tongs to dunk the frozen balls of dough individually into the melted margarine or butter.
Then coat each ball with the dry mixture and place in Bundt pan.
Pour remaining margarine or butter and dry mixture over the dough.
Cover with a tea towel and let rise overnight or for no less than 6 hours on the kitchen counter.
Dough should rise above edge of pan.
Heat oven to 350°. Cook for 20 to 25 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: orange glaze cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs one at a time.
Add soda to buttermilk, then add alternately with sifted flour.
Combine floured dates, nuts and orange rind and add to cake batter.
Bake in tube or loaf pan 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Wash, core, peel and slice apples into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
With pastry blender, mix brown sugar, flour, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, butter and oats until crumbly.
Sprinkle or spread crumbs over apples. Bake for 30 minutes and serve.

title: danish baked fish fillets
directions: Put fish, patted dry, in single layer in baking dish.
Cover with broth and lemon juice.
Salt lightly .
Bake, covered, 10 to 15 minutes, until opaque.
Transfer to platter.
If liquid is less than 1 cup, add broth.
Melt butter over medium heat in skillet. Stir in flour, cook, don't brown.
Remove from heat.
Gradually stir in liquid over heat until thick.
Blend in sour cream and dill.
Spoon over fish.
Bake at 400°, uncovered, until sauce is bubbly, 10 to 12 minutes.

title: heavenly chocolate mousse
directions: In a microwave or double boiler, heat chocolate, 1/4 cup water, and butter until the chocolate and butter are melted. Cool for 10 minutes. In a small, heavy saucepan, whisk egg yolks, sugar, and remaining water. Cook and stir over low heat until mixture reaches 160 (about 1 - 2 minutes). Remove from the heat; whisk in chocolate mixture. Set saucepan in ice and stir until cooled, about 5 - 10 minutes, Fold in whipped cream. Spoon into dessert dishes. Refrigerate for at least 4 hours.

title: stuffed mushroom potato
directions: Put potato in the microwave and cook.
Meanwhile, stir-fry onion and mushrooms in a nonstick skillet.
When potato is done and cooled, cut off top.
Dig out the middle.
Take onion, mushrooms and potato middle and mix together in a bowl.
Stuff mixture back into the potato and heat again in microwave.
Top with sour cream.

title: chipped beef cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese, chipped beef, onion, m.s.g. and Worcestershire sauce in bowl; mix well.
Shape into 2 balls on waxed paper.
Chill for 3 hours or longer.
Roll in pecans.
Place on serving plates.
Yield:
80 servings.

title: german sauerkraut
directions: Cook sauerkraut with fresh pig hock approxiately one hour. Take raw potato and add to sauerkraut.
Cook until thickened.
Add applesauce; heat until warm. Serve with roast pork and mashed potatoes.

title: wonderous whipped cream
directions: Pour milk into a small stainless steel bowl.
Set in freezer until ice crystals start to form.
Use mixer and thicken by beating in dry milk.
Continue on high until soft peaks form.
Pour in honey and continue to beat until stiff peaks form.
Whip up just before serving.
Contains 12 calories and 0.1 g fat per 2 tablespoons.

title: choco-peanut butter tortillas
directions: Spread peanut butter all over tortillas.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on.
Roll it.
Cut it.
Stick in the toothpick.

title: roasted vegetables with rotini
directions: Chop peppers into cubes and combine with onion.
Pour olive oil and mustard over vegetables, stirring well.
Spread vegetables in a large, greased baking dish.
Bake vegetables at 400° for approximately 20 minutes or until tender.

title: quaker oats meat loaf
directions: Basically combine all ingredients until well mixed.
(An electric mixer is very useful.)
Form into either a loaf pan or other pan.
Bake at 350°F for about an hour.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Then add sifted dry ingredients, alternately with buttermilk.
Add flavoring.
Add vinegar and soda.
Mix until well blended.
Bake in 3 greased layer pans and lightly floured.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix with oil; add eggs, one at a time.
Add jello and lemon extract and beat well.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: grammy's whipped cream icing
directions: In a leak-proof container, mix milk and flour; shake until well mixed. Pour mixture into a medium saucepan and cook slowly over low heat. Continually stir mixture. Cook until mixture is thick. There should be no lumps. Let cool completely.

title: chocolate cake
directions: This cake is a recipe passed down to my mother from my great aunt who lived to be 101 years old.
She used it many times before me, and I use it very often now.
I will pass it on to my niece.

title: tuna swiss pie
directions: Pierce pie shell thoroughly with fork.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes, then remove from oven.
In large bowl, toss tuna, cheese and onion; spoon this into pie shell.
Stir remaining ingredients together.
Slowly pour over tuna mixture.
Bake 50 minutes in 350° oven or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: cyclone cornbread
directions: Prepare muffin mix according to directions and add extra ingredients.
Bake about 5 to 10 minutes longer than box recommends.

title: u.s. 31 barbecue sauce
directions: Cook slow for several hours, then add shredded meat and reheat.
(I make one-half of all amounts.)

title: chili
directions: Fry hamburger and onions; drain.
Put everything else in and cook for 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: graveyard
directions: Crush Oreo cookies.
Put chocolate pudding in pan. Mix in crushed Oreos. Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Decorate with whip cream.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Optional:
Combine white wine, green onion and parsley.
Pour over golden brown chicken.

title: chicken alfredo
directions: In large deep saucepan, cook egg noodles to desired doneness as directed on package.
Combine margarine and milk with noodles. Heat until margarine melts, stirring gently, until heated through. Remove from heat.
Toss with Parmesan cheese.

title: screw ball cake
