directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, soda and cocoa. Add water, oil, egg, vinegar and vanilla. Bake on a cookie sheet at 325° for 30 minutes. Frost with whipped cream icing.

title: french string bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Follow directions on package for preparing string beans.
Heat soup (just as is, not diluted).
Pour string beans into casserole dish and add soup.
Top with onion rings.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Canned French string beans may be substituted for frozen ones.

title: ginger beans with luncheon meat
directions: Combine beans, gingersnap crumbs, catsup, molasses and salt; turn into 1-quart casserole.
Cut luncheon meat into six slices; place on top of beans.
Bake, covered, in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: "gabbert" gravy(grandmother's family recipe)
directions: Cook cornbread and slice open-faced on dinner plate.
Tear lettuce and spread over cornbread.
Slice radishes over lettuce. Next, dice onions over radishes.
Top with generous amount of crumbled bacon.
Finally, pour thin milk gravy over mixture.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Eat, enjoy and chase with Pepto-Bismol.

title: baked yellow squash
directions: Cook squash, onion and carrots in salt water for 5 minutes. Heat sour cream, chicken soup and butter.
Make Stove Top dressing.
Fill bottom of casserole with dressing (save 1/2 of dressing for top of casserole).
Drain squash; mix with soup mixture and put over layer of filling in casserole.
Garnish top with rest of dressing.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cake mix gobs
directions: Mix all ingredients and drop onto greased cookie sheet by tablespoon.
Leave at least 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes good lunch cookies.
Fill with favorite icing.

title: lemon drops
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: moist chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients with eggs, milk, oil and vanilla. Beat 2 minutes.
Hand stir in boiling water.
Batter will be thin. Bake at 350°.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes for round layers and 35 to 40 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: the best little chocolate pie in texas
directions: Mix sugar, salt, and cornstarch.
Then combine with scalded milk. Add chocolate.
Cook slowly over low heat in a heavy pan or double boiler, stirring constantly, for 15 to 20 minutes.
Beat egg yolks. Stir small amount of hot mixture into the yolks.
Then return the yolk-chocolate mixture to the pan (this prevents the eggs from cooking).
Cook for 5 more minutes.
Add butter and vanilla and let cool to room temperature.
(To prevent a crust from forming on the custard, cover with clear plastic wrap or wax paper).
Use reserved egg whites for meringue.
Bake at 325° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar and butter. Add 2 eggs at a time.
Add flour. Mix until velvety.
Pour into pan and cook at 350° until brown, about 50 to 60 minutes.

title: corn flake macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites and vanilla until foamy.
Gradually add sugar while beating.
Continue to beat until stiff and glossy.
Fold in corn flakes, nuts and coconut.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls into a well-greased baking sheet.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 12 minutes.
Remove from baking sheet and cool on wire rack.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix together and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hard tack candy
directions: Cook until forms a hard string in cold water.
Add flavoring and color (if desired).
Pour onto greased cookie sheet.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs on high for 5 minutes.
Gradually beat in sugar. Stir in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Stir in flour, baking powder, spices and salt.
Spread on 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Top with nuts.
Bake 15 minutes at 375°.
Don't overbake!

title: mud pie
directions: Melt margarine; stir in nuts and flour.
Press into 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool crust.

title: v-8 soup
directions: Put all ingredients (except spinach) in a large Dutch oven. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Serve and garnish with spinach.

title: custard pie
directions: Blend eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla.
Gradually stir in scalded milk.
Pour into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg. Bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cool on rack, then chill.

title: creamy chicken and wild rice soup
directions: Melt butter in large pan over medium heat.
Stir in flour until smooth and bubbly (1 minute).
Add milk and chicken broth. Continue cooking, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a full boil (5 to 7 minutes).
Boil 1 minute.
Add all remaining ingredients except sour cream.
Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crispy tender (4 to 6 minutes). Stir in sour cream.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Brown pork in hot fat.
Add water, cover and simmer for 1 hour.
Combine cornstarch, salt, brown sugar, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce; cook, stirring until slightly thickened. Pour sauce over hot pork; let stand 10 minutes.
Add green peppers, onion, carrots and pineapple chunks.
Cook 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add wet ingredients, including melted shortening or oil.
Chill in refrigerator.
Form in 1-inch balls, roll in sugar and place on cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: cocoa peanut butter cookies(kisses)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, cocoa and soda. Set aside. Beat butter and peanut butter until creamy, then add 1/3 cup sugar and brown sugar. Beat until fluffy.
Mix in egg, milk and vanilla. Beat until smooth.
On low speed, put in flour mixture just until blended.
Shape into heaping teaspoonful balls.
Roll balls in 1/4 cup sugar to coat them. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 12 minutes until firm.
Remove from oven.
Immediately press Kiss on top of cookie, pressing firmly.
Let cool.

title: rolls
directions: Mix
the eggs, cold water and sugar in
a
large
bowl. Mix in
small bowl the oleo, boiling water
and
Crisco.
Let oleo melt and mixture cool.
Dissolve 2 packages
or
cakes of yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Mix
all
other
ingredients together in largest bowl.
Add 7 cups
self-rising flour.
Mix well, cover and let stand.
Cook at 450° for
7 to 10 minutes. Store remainder in refrigerator in
airtight
container.
Will keep several days.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: In a crock-pot, add thawed chicken breast, can of soup, salt and pepper.
In microwave or stove top, melt chicken bouillon in 1/3 cup water.
Add to crock-pot.
Cook on low 5 to 6 hours or high 3 to 4 hours.
Cook noodles on stove top.
Pour chicken and sauce over noodles.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add onions and milk.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot shortening, about 3 inches deep.
Cook until golden brown.

title: rudolph sandwich
directions: Trim the crusts off slices of bread.
Cut each slice of bread into two triangles.
Spread peanut butter on each triangle. Decorate with raisins for eyes, an M&M for a nose and pretzels for antlers.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, butter, milk and cocoa in a large kettle. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, to dissolve sugar.
Add vanilla; let boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter and oats.
You may spoon out onto wax paper or pour onto cookie sheet and cut into squares.
Be sure mixture comes to a full rolling boil for 1 minute.

title: christmas gingerboys
directions: Cut with Christmas cookie cutters and bake at 350°.
(Do not overbake.)
Frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: farm apple pan pie(serves 24)
directions: Roll out half the pastry and use to line 15 1/2 x 10 x 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle lemon juice on apples.
Place half the apples in bottom of pastry lined pan, spreading evenly. Combine remaining ingredients, except apples.
Sprinkle half the mixture over apples in pan.
Spread remaining apples on top. Sprinkle with remaining sugar-spice mixture.
Top with remaining pastry, rolled out, seal and crimp edges.
Brush with milk. Sprinkle with a little sugar and cut vents or prick with fork. Bake in hot oven (400°) for 50 minutes.
When cool, drizzle with 1 cup confectioners
sugar mixed with 2 tablespoons milk.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: mary's marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Add chicken, fish or beef to a large Ziploc bag and set into pan to fit.
Add marinade. Press out most of air and zip up bag.
Coat food.
Let sit in fridge 2 to 24
hours, turning bag to coat food every so often.

title: soda cracker candy
directions: Boil sugar and cream for 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter.
Pour over saltines.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: philadelphia pasta
directions: Cook macaroni for 20 minutes.
Drain and rinse in cold water. Add all ingredients together and allow to marinate in dressing for 2 hours in refrigerator.
Drain off dressing before serving.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: pocket bread
directions: Mix sugar, salt and water in bowl; cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle 1 package yeast over mixture and allow to dissolve.
Add 1 cup flour; mix and add remaining flour.
Turn dough on floured surface and knead thoroughly.
Divide into 10 small pieces.
Roll into a ball.
With roller, roll each ball into a 5-inch circle and place on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 500° for 5 to 7 minutes until puff is golden brown.
Remove and rub with butter.

title: aunt mag's pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening real well.
Add eggs one at a time. Stir in flour with wooden spoon.
Do not use electric mixer!
Add flavoring of your choice.
Bake at 300° to 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: rigatoni in tomato basil sauce
directions: Cook rigatoni in 4 qts. boiling water until al dente.
Set aside.
Using a large frying pan, saute garlic and zucchini in olive oil.
Add Tomato Basil sauce.
Simmer on low 20-30 mins.
Add rigatoni and simmer till hot.

title: choco-dot pumpkin cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda, salt and spices together.
In separate bowl, beat eggs until foamy, then add pumpkin, vegetable oil and whole bran cereal.
Add sifted ingredients to cereal mixture, stirring only until combined.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Spread into greased and floured Bundt cake pan and bake for 70 minutes at 350°.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix yogurt and honey.
Put 1 slice pineapple in each dish. Put 1 teaspoon of yogurt mixture in the middle.
Serve.

title: reese's pieces
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients with hands.
Pat into shallow pan. Melt and pour chocolate over mixture.
Score while warm. Refrigerate at least 2 hours to set.
Set out for a while before eating.

title: sour cream corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 400° for about 30 minutes or until done.
Cook in 10-inch iron skillet.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix syrup, sugar, flour, butter and eggs together.
Add pecans last.
Bake at 300° for about 45 minutes.

title: monkey bread(microwave recipe)
directions: In a shallow 1-quart microwave-safe casserole or 8-inch round glass dish, combine brown sugar, butter and water.
Microwave on High for 1 minute, uncovered.
Stir to melt butter.
Stir in nuts.

title: parmesan potatoes
directions: Combine cheese, flour, salt and pepper and batter potatoes. Slightly overlap slices in single layer in Pyrex dish or biscuit pan. Drizzle with margarine. Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 40 minutes or until tender.

title: chicken pepper sauce
directions: Heat gravy mix, water, sour cream and green pepper to boiling.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix and stir in order given:
flour, soda, baking powder, salt, shortening, peanut butter and Sweet 'N Low.
Add beaten egg.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: ham and potato casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Combine sour cream and soup in a 9 x 9 inch pan. Add hash browns, ham and cheese. Cover and bake for 50 minutes, stirring once at 25 minutes. Remove from oven when hot and bubbly. Sprinkle with crushed croutons, let stand 10 minutes before serving.
tags: cream of chicken soup or mushroom soup

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine all ingredients except coconut in mixing bowl or blender.
Blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into a greased 9-inch deep pie pan.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle coconut over top.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: hocus-pocus crispies
directions: Unroll crescent dough into 2 long rectangles.
Place together, overlapping edges, to form 13 x 9-inch rectangle.
Firmly press perforations and edges to seal them.
Spread with margarine. Combine brown sugar, nuts and cinnamon.
Sprinkle evenly over margarine.
Starting at shorter side, roll up sealing long edge. Cut into 8 slices.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten out each one with hand to a 4-inch circle.
Sprinkle each with about 1/2 teaspoon granulated sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or just until golden brown.
Immediately remove from cookie sheet and place on wire racks to cool.
Makes 8 rolls.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, water and syrup. Bring to rolling boil and add peanuts. Cook slowly until peanuts are done, about 25 to 30 minutes. When nuts start popping, remove from heat and add soda. Mix well and pour on buttered pan or cookie sheet. When cool, break in pieces. Store in airtight container.

title: pear preserves
directions: Select hard green pears. Wash, peel and core. Slice thin and place in large pan. Add sugar and mix thoroughly with pears. Let stand 8 to 10 hours. Slice lemon thin, removing seeds, and add to pears. Bring to boil quickly over high heat, stirring constantly until sugar is dissolved. Boil rapidly, stirring frequently, until pears are transparent and syrup thickens. The cooking time will depend on the type of pears. Pour at once into hot sterilized jars and seal.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Prepare pastry.
Combine the sugar, nutmeg, flour and salt. Add dry ingredients to the beaten eggs; beat smooth.
Stir in the rhubarb slices.
Pour mixture into prepared pie plate.
Dot with the butter.
Adjust lattice top.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Cream Cheddar cheese with cream cheese.
Add spices and pecans. You may form cheese in a ball or long roll.
Sprinkle chili powder on wax paper.
Roll cheese in chili powder.
Chill until firm and serve with crackers.

title: maple cream coffee treat
directions: Mix together in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, brown sugar, nuts, maple syrup and 1/4 cup margarine.
Blend and mix until smooth in separate bowl, cream cheese, powdered sugar and 2 tablespoons margarine.
Separate biscuit dough into 20 biscuits; press or roll each to a 4-inch circle.
Spoon 1 tablespoon cream cheese mixture onto center of each biscuit.
Overlap dough over filling, forming finger-shaped rolls.
Place rolls seam side down in a row of 10 over syrup mixture in pan.
Make 2 rows.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool 3 minutes.
Turn onto serving plate or waxed paper.

title: 5-cup salad
directions: Drain fruit and fold in rest of ingredients.
Chill.

title: hot pepper jelly
directions: Boil peppers and vinegar 1 minute, then skin off foam.
Add sugar; boil 5 minutes more.
Let set for 5 minutes, put in jars and seal.

title: southwestern egg bake
directions: Heat oven to 400°. Spray rectangular baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2 inches, with nonstick cooking spray. Mix stuffing, corn, chilies, sour cream and 1 egg in large bowl. Spread evenly in baking dish. Make 6 indentations in stuffing mixture with back of spoon. Break 1 egg into each indentation. Pierce yolk of each egg with fork. Bake uncovered 20 to 25 minutes or until egg whites and yolks are not runny. Sprinkle cheese over stuffing mixture. Bake 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve with salsa.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Cool in refrigerator before rolling into small balls.
Dip in chocolate.

title: antipasto
directions: Put all ingredients in a large pot. Bring to boil and stir well.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Cool slightly. Put in a jar or covered dish. Refrigerate at least 24 hours.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Roll cookie dough out on a pizza pan or cookie sheet.
Bake then let cool.
Top with a mixture of cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Top with strawberry glaze and any kind of fruits.
Top with whipped cream and nuts, if desired.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Place the potatoes and onion on a large piece of heavy-duty foil; dot with butter.
Combine the cheese, parsley, Worcestershire, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle over potatoes.
Fold foil up around potatoes and add broth.
Seal the edges of foil well.
Grill, covered, over medium coals for 35 to 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Serves 4 to 6.
Great for cookouts!

title: gingersnap cookies
directions: Combine shortening, brown sugar and egg (unbeaten).
Mix until fluffy.
Add molasses and beat well.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, ginger, cinnamon and cloves.
Mix well.
Chill dough thoroughly.
Shape into 1-inch balls and roll in granulated sugar. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes on ungreased baking sheets.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: Combine peanut butter and butter; blending well.
Gradually add sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, beating well.
Stir in almond extract.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; stir well.
Spread mixture evenly in a greased 9-inch square pan, bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool completely in pan and cut into 1 1/2-inch squares.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: cocoa(yields 4 servings)
directions: Place cocoa, sugar and water in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Heat in microwave on High for 30 to 60 seconds or until mixture boils. Stir in milk and salt.
Heat in microwave for 6 to 8 minutes or until warmed.

title: 4 in one casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add celery and fry together until meat is browned.
Layer all ingredients in a casserole dish, except soup, then pour soup and water over ingredients and bake 1 hour or until vegetables are done in a 350° oven.

title: jennie's #1 scratch angel food cake
directions: Separate egg whites and discard yolks.
Let egg whites stand at room temperature while you prepare flour.
Sift flour and powdered sugar twice.
Mix egg whites, vanilla and cream of tartar.
Mix on low for a minute or so, then increase speed of mixer by two until mixing on high.
When soft peaks begin to form, beat in the granulated sugar, 1/4 cup at a time.
Beat on high until stiff peaks stand when mixer is turned off.
Stir in (by hand) the flour mixture (just until mixed, don't overmix).

title: twenty minute cassoulet
directions: Brown sausage in Dutch oven or large saucepan over medium heat, stirring frequently.
With slotted spoon, remove sausage; set aside.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In 1-quart casserole, combine water, macaroni and salt. Microcook uncovered 7 to 8 minutes, stirring twice.
Drain.
In same casserole, microcook onion in oleo about 1 1/2 minutes. Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Stir in milk and Worcestershire sauce.
Microcook uncovered until thick and bubbly, 2 to 3 minutes, stirring 3 to 4 times.
Stir in cheese until it is melted.
Stir in macaroni.
Microcook 1 to 2 minutes, stirring once or twice.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cook carrots until tender.
Mix onion, bell pepper, tomato soup, oil, sugar, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and salt and pour over cooled carrots.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream together sugar, butter and salt until mixture is fluffy, light and creamy.
Add eggs and continue creaming.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately with applesauce.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour batter into greased and floured baking pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Serves 50.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Roll into balls.
Brown on 3 sides.
Put in gravy (sauce) to complete cooking.

title: lemon fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Reserve 3/4 cup of dredged fruits and nuts, toss well.
Add flour, a little at a time, to cream mixture, then add lemon extract.
When well combined, add flour dredged fruit and nuts.
Bake at 275° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours in a greased tube pan which you have lined the bottom of with greased brown paper (paper bag) cut to fit.
Test for doneness.

title: mexican cheese casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Mix soup, tomatoes, butter, onion and broth together.
Place layer of crushed chips in a 9 x 12-inch dish.
Top with half of shredded chicken.
Pour half of soup mixture on top.
Repeat again with chips, chicken and soup.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with cheese.
Bake until cheese is melted.

title: applesauce pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, syrup, vanilla, applesauce and pecans.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes.
This is very good and not so sweet.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: lime refrigerator pie
directions: Thaw limeade or lemonade until mushy.
Mix with Cool Whip and milk.
Pour into pie shell.
Put in freezer and take out 20 minutes before serving.

title: corned beef sandwiches
directions: Mix ingredients together; spread on day old bread.

title: shrimp cocktail
directions: In large pan, heat 4 cups water and salt to boiling; add shrimp and cook over low heat until shrimp turn pink, about 3 minutes; drain.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice cooked potatoes.
Chop celery, onions, eggs and pepper. Mix all ingredients well together.
Makes about 3 gallons.
Serves 50.

title: fish chowder
directions: Cube salt pork and fry until crisp, not burned.
Remove pork pieces and fry chopped onions until tender, do not let burn.
Add to the chopped potatoes in a large kettle.
Cover (barely) with water.
Cook until potatoes are just tender.
Lay fish over the potatoes and cook just until fish flakes.
Add the milks, if not enough liquid add some more milk.
Add butter, salt and pepper to taste.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to directions.
Pour 1/2 of the mixture in a greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°. Melt caramels with milk over low heat to make sauce.
Remove cake from the oven after 10 minutes and pour sauce over the cake. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and nuts.
Pour remaining batter over cake and sauce.
Bake an additional 17 to 20 minutes longer or until done.

title: banana cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pan).
Mix dry and wet ingredients separately and then together.
Pour into a small (8 x 8-inch or 9 x 9-inch) pan.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pan) for 30 to 35 minutes.
Recipe can be doubled (9 x 13-inch pan); add 10 minutes or so to baking time.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together the potatoes, egg yolks, margarine, sugar and baking powder.
Into this mixture, fold egg whites and pecans. Place into buttered casserole dish or baking ring.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in a 350° oven.
Serves 8.

title: zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini into 1/4-inch slices.
Cook and stir zucchini and remaining ingredients, except tomatoes, in a 10-inch skillet until heated through.
Cover and cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisp-tender (5 minutes).
Add tomatoes.
Cover and cook over low heat just until tomatoes are heated through (3 minutes).
Sprinkle with snipped parsley and grated Parmesan cheese.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Put yeast in large bowl, add lukewarm water and stir until dissolved.
Add salt, sugar, eggs, oil, water and flour.
Mix well. Cover with waxed paper and chill overnight.
Break off bits of dough, roll into balls and arrange in greased pan or on cookie sheet.
(Three small balls in muffin pan will make cloverleaf rolls, or roll dough with rolling pin into circle, cut into triangles and roll into crescents.)
Let rise until doubled in size, about 3 hours.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 450°.
Brush with butter or margarine.

title: beef and veggies casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onions.
Add cream and soup.
Mix. Simmer.
Prepare vegetables.
Drain and add to mixture.
Serve over rice.

title: hash brown potatoes
directions: Grease glass 9 x 13-inch pan with oleo; put in partially thawed potatoes.
Mix soup, milk, salt and pepper; pour over potatoes.
Melt oleo and pour over top.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil.
Crumble onion rings over top and brown 5 to 10 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes in round slices.
Add onion and salt; boil 10 minutes.
Cover bottom of dish with milk.
Drain potato mixture and put in casserole on top of milk.
Add oleo. Bake 15 to 20	minutes at 350°.
Take out of oven and top with enough Velveeta
cheese
to
cover potato mixture.
Let cheese melt. Sprinkle
with
grated
Cheddar
cheese.
Let melt.
So good!

title: glass candy
directions: Melt oleo and chips. Cool.
Line cookie sheet with foil paper. Sprinkle
coconut	 over	paper.	Mix
chocolate	and marshmallows and pat down on coconut.
Top with coconut.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and press in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix well remaining ingredients and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine salt, sugar, dry mustard, pepper, garlic, lemon juice, water, corn oil and onion in a jar.
Cover tightly; shake until thoroughly blended.
Chill.
Just before serving, combine spinach and mushrooms or radishes in large salad bowl.
Pour on dressing and toss.
Yields 8 servings.

title: rita's good bars
directions: Melt caramels and water in double boiler over low heat.
Mix with Rice Krispies and peanuts.
Press mixture into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put chocolate chips and butterscotch chips on top. Put into a 200° oven for 5 to 8 minutes.
Take out of oven and spread on like frosting.

title: low cholesterol chocolate cake or cupcakes
directions: Do not grease pan!

title: meat loaf pinwheels
directions: You will need a 12 x 10-inch piece of aluminum foil and a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: our favorite fried rice
directions: Remove outer skin and cut onions in quarters.
Place in shallow
baking
dish that has been buttered.
Dot onions with butter;
sprinkle
on
a
few
bread
crumbs, lots of Parmesan cheese,
black
pepper and a little salt.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until onions are fork-tender.

title: spicy cajun popcorn topping
directions: Place in a microwave-safe bowl and microwave for 30 to 45 seconds on High until butter is melted.
Keep warm. Add to popcorn as desired.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Combine ingredients and mix until well blended. Pour into a 12-cup Bundt pan sprayed with Pam. Cook 50 to 60 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven and poke holes in cake with fork. Glaze as follows:

title: southwest stew
directions: In skillet, brown meat and onions; drain fat.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese, and bring to a boil, simmering 15 to 20 minutes.
Add shredded cheese on top.

title: onion patties
directions: Add enough cold water to make a paste.
Add onions.
Fry by teaspoon.
Deep fry until golden brown.

title: party log
directions: Puree beef, mayonnaise, garlic, paprika, worcestershire sauce, cayenne pepper, and green onions.
With hand mixer, combine beef mixture with cream cheese, this will be very thick.
Slowly add shredded cheese.
When combined well, roll into log. Refrigerate.
Roll in chopped almonds just before serving.
Serve with variety of crackers.

title: pecan logs
directions: Mix powdered sugar and marshmallow cream.
Form rolls and chill.
Melt caramels and water.
Dip rolls in and roll in nuts. Keep refrigerated.

title: oven baked french fries
directions: Can also add red pepper, chili powder and black pepper.

title: quick jello dessert
directions: Combine Jell-O, cottage cheese, Cool Whip, pecan pieces and pineapple.
Stir together and chill.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; chop and drain.
Mix other ingredients.
Put into buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna steaks
directions: Cut onion into quarters.
Combine all ingredients except tuna and blend in blender or food processor.
Process until smooth. Place tuna in large glass baking dish.
Pour sauce over fish and turn to coat with pepper sauce.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Preheat grill.
Place tuna on well-greased grill over medium heat.
May use fresh jalapenos or other peppers instead of jar of peppers.
May be made without vermouth.
Tastes great.

title: lemon pudding cake
directions: *For Saucy Pudding Cake, increase milk to 1 cup.

title: blonde brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into 9 x 12-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and lightly flour two 9 x 1 1/2-inch round baking pans.

title: pasta primavera
directions: Measure oil into a large skillet or wok. Add garlic, broccoli, carrot, salt and pepper.
Saute, stirring, 3 minutes. Turn off heat to preserve bright color.
Cook pasta; drain. Return to pot to keep warm. To skillet, add onions, tomatoes and wine. Cover and cook 3 minutes. Serve vegetables over pasta. Top with Parmesan.

title: topsy-turvy tuna-lemon pie
directions: Start heating oven to 400°.
Grease 8-inch round shallow casserole.
Arrange lemon slices in bottom of dish.
Mix tuna, onion, green pepper, bread crumbs, mustard, lemon juice, catsup and egg; spread over lemon slices.
Top with cheese slices.
With fork, stir milk into biscuit mix to make soft dough.
Spread dough over cheese layer.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Melt marshmallows and strawberry juice over low heat, folding until mixture is smooth.
Add coloring and cool.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in sugar until meringue peaks.
Add salt, then gently whip in the cooled marshmallow mixture.
Fill pastry shell with very firm ice cream.
Cover with layer of strawberries.
Top with meringue swirled gaily.
Place in boiler about 3 to 6-inches away from flame; brown quickly.
Tuck unstemmed strawberries in swirl and serve immediately.

title: dump cake
directions: Bring Crisco, water, oleo and cocoa to a boil and dump in bowl with flour and sugar.
Mix well.
Dump in buttermilk, soda, eggs and vanilla.
Beat 2 minutes on medium speed.
Mixture will be thin.
Pour into greased and floured 11 x 16-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: lime pickles
directions: Soak the cucumber slices in the lime and water mixture for 24 hours.
Stir these gently with a wooden spoon, to keep lime from settling to the bottom, 5 or 6 times during the soaking period. Remove pickles from the lime water.
Wash well and soak 3 to 4 hours in plain cold water.
Remove pickles from this water; rinse again.
Mix vinegar mixture.
Put pickles in this mix.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Next boil pickles in vinegar mixture for 35 minutes.
Can in sterilized cans and seal.

title: pastry
directions: Combine flour, margarine and salt in food processor.
Whirl until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir together egg yolk and water in small cup.
Add to processor.
Pulse until mixture is just combined and starts to mass together.
Remove and flatten into dish.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill until firm.
Roll into crust.

title: eggs for brunch
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Cut bacon in small pieces and brown until crisp. Drain excess fat. Add tomatoes, onion and garlic to bacon. Heat through. Divide into 4 individual baking dishes. Carefully slip 1 egg on top of each mixture. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Bake for 20-25 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Beat egg yolks with the juice of lemons.
Add Eagle Brand milk and mix well.

title: squash casserole
directions: In skillet, cook chicken in a little bit of oil.
Cook squash and onion in boiling water (about 3 minutes).
Squash must be a little crisp.
Drain squash and combine with chicken, chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in carrots; salt to taste.
Combine stuffing mix and butter; divide in half.
Spread 1/2 stuffing in a 12 x 7 x 2-inch dish.
Spread squash mixture over stuffing.
Spread rest of stuffing over squash.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: nannie's macaroni
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling water with salt until tender.
Drain. In saucepan, melt 3 tablespoons butter.
Blend in flour, 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add onions and cheese sauce with macaroni.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until heated through.
Makes 6 servings.

title: squash parmesan
directions: Cut
unpeeled
squash
lengthwise into 1/4 inch slices. In large
bowl,
beat	together
eggs and water.
Coat squash slices in	flour,	dip
in
egg mixture, then coat with bread crumbs.
In large
skillet,
cook
squash
slices
in a small amount
of hot oil until lightly browned, turning once.
Drain on paper toweling.
In bottom on 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish, spread bottom with sauce, about 1/2 cup.	Layer squash slices, cheese and meat; cover
with sauce.	Repeat layers.	Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake uncovered
in
350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Cut up onion and put in meat, then add egg, then one half can of undiluted cream of celery soup.
Mash up crackers and add to meat, enough to make it stick together in a ball.
Cook for half hour, pour off any grease, then add the mixture of the can of tomatoes and rest of soup and pour over meat loaf and cook another half hour, should be done by then.

title: judy's curried fruit
directions: Make your sauce.
Layer drained fruit.
Cover with sauce.
Let set in refrigerator overnight.
Pour maraschino cherries with juice on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
This is great warmed over.

title: never-fail peanut butter fudge
directions: In a heavy saucepan, mix together the peanut butter and margarine. Stir until melted. While hot, add vanilla, cocoa and powdered sugar. Stir until blended and smooth. Pat into a pie plate. Cool and enjoy! This recipe never fails -- not ever! Makes about 20 pieces.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Combine all ingredients, reserving 3/4 cup cheese.
Pour mixture into a greased 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Remove from oven; sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake 10 more minutes.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: porcini gnocchi
directions: Wash and soak the dry porcini mushrooms in warm water until soft.
Reserve liquid and reduce to about 3 tablespoons. Puree mushrooms to a paste in food processor.
Add Ricotta, Parmigiano, egg and reduce liquid to a puree until incorporated.
In mixer, add salt, pepper and flour - mix until flour is absorbed on the pulse cycle (it should be slightly sticky and soft).
Let rest for 1 hour in the refrigerator, then roll out sections into 1/2-inch tubes.
Cut each tube on a bias.
This forms the "gnocchi." Bring water to a boil and drop gnocchi in.
Cook until they float. Strain.
In the same pan melt 1 stick of butter.
Pour gnocchi back in.
Season with salt and pepper and add chopped parsley.

title: chicken and dumplin stew
directions: Combine chicken, potatoes and Veg-All.
Cook until potatoes are done.
Combine Bisquick and water in bowl.
Drop by spoonfuls on top of stew.
Cook until dumplins are done.

title: marinade recipe
directions: Whisk all ingredients together. Soak meat at least 3 hours in marinade. Can soak overnight. Will turn chicken brown in color.

title: three-in-one dip
directions: Mix all ingredients at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Refrigerate.
Serve with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.
Yield: 2 cups.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease an 8-inch square baking dish; set aside.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions. Meanwhile, in large bowl, combine soup, milk, Parmesan and pepper. Stir in chicken and spinach.
Drain spaghetti; place in bottom of baking dish.
Pour chicken mixture over top of spaghetti; stir until well combined.
Bake, covered for 50 to 60 minutes, until bubbly.
Serves 4.

title: buckeye cookies
directions: Combine Rice Krispies, butter, sugar and crunchy peanut butter. Work well using your hands.
Roll into small balls.
Melt chips and paraffin in top of a double boiler.
Dip cookies into this.
Use a fork or toothpick.
Cool on wax paper.
Makes approximately 65.

title: minty chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly grease 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Melt chocolate and butter in microwave.
Cool.
Beat eggs and sugar until thick in medium size bowl.
Add nuts, flour and chocolate mixture; stir until smooth.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes and cool.

title: christmas nut roll
directions: Melt margarine and marshmallows.
Add crushed crackers.
Mix in cut cherries.
Stir and mix well.
Add nuts and mix.
Shape into roll; chill overnight.
Slice to serve.

title: april fools dirt cake
directions: You will also need 8-inch plastic flowerpot (new), 2 plastic drinking straws, 2 silk flowers and 8 gummy worms.

title: dump cake
directions: Layer in a 9 x 13 pan in the following order: Pineapple with juice first. Spoon pie filling on top. Add cake mix. Sprinkle nuts on cake mix. Put butter slices on top. Bake at 350° for 48 to 53 minutes.

title: chocolate upside-down cake or earthquake cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Place nuts and coconut in the bottom of the pan.
Prepare cake mix according to package directions and pour this over nuts and coconut.
Mix butter, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Drop by spoonfuls over cake. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: "join the party" salad
directions: Layer lettuce, torn in bite-sized pieces, celery, green pepper, onions, radishes and peas in a large glass salad bowl. Spread with mayonnaise and top with sliced egg, bacon and cheese. Cover and refrigerate for 12 to 24 hours.
Toss before serving.

title: potato cups
directions: Grate your potatoes finely.
Mix grated potatoes, flour, salt and baking powder.
Heat butter on griddle and fry until golden brown.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Blend and heat soups, milk and 2/3 stick of margarine.
When melted, add rice and stir.
(Can add dried vegetables for color.) Pour mixture into greased pan.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan or larger. Fill it only 2/3 full (rice swells).

title: potato cake
directions: Cream together sugar, shortening and cocoa.
Add eggs and mashed potatoes.
Dissolve soda in small amount of warm water. Add soda and buttermilk.
Stir in flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Add vanilla.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts, raisins and pear preserves.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: rolled sugar cookies(makes 85 small 2-inch cookies)
directions: Let butter stand until soft.
Add granulated sugar, egg, milk and vanilla; mix thoroughly.
Sift flour and baking powder together; add slowly while mixing.
Chill for 1/2 hour.

title: cold oven pound cake
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and beat at medium speed for 20 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and place in cold oven.
Turn on oven and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: potato soup(9 servings)
directions: Put all ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer covered for 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: argentine spinach pie (torta pascualina)
directions: Cook spinach, drain and chop finely.
Saute onion in hot oil. Combine spinach, onion and remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie shell.
Arrange top crust and seal.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve hot in wedges.

title: velveeta roll
directions: Put Velveeta cheese between two sheets of wax paper and roll very thin.
Spread cream cheese over rolled Velveeta.
In small mixing bowl, mix green onions, pecans, pimentos, green chilies, bacon bits and red pepper.
Mix well and spread over cheese evenly.
Start rolling, with the help of wax paper under cheese. After roll is made, refrigerate until firm.
Slice and serve with favorite crackers.
Good for the holidays.

title: low-fat cream cheese pound cake
directions: Bring cheese, margarine and eggs to room temperature. Separate egg yolks and whites.
Mix cream cheese and margarine. Add egg whites, sugar and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.
Add cake flour and mix until consistent.
Pour into a Bundt pan and bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let cool before removing from pan.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Combine all ingredients except tomato sauce.
Make into balls; pour tomato sauce over balls and bake 3 hours at 350°.

title: rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Beat together.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour or until brown.

title: breakfast hash
directions: Using a large skillet, brown potatoes in melted butter. Season with salt and pepper. Add smokey links and sweet green pepper. If you desire, you can also add onion. Beat eggs, then add to mixture in skillet. Cook, stirring often until eggs are done. Serves 4.

title: mabo dofu
directions: Cut tofu into 1/2-inch cubes.
Set aside and drain well.
Heat oil in skillet.
Add ginger, garlic, green onions and red pepper and stir over high heat.
Brown beef.
Add 1/2 tablespoon soy sauce and reduce to medium heat.
Add ketchup, remainder of soy sauce, wine and soup stock.
Bring to a boil.
Add cornstarch liquid and stir until thickened.
Add green peas.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, salt and cornstarch, stirring constantly, until comes to a boil and thickens.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin; cool slightly.
Add berries; pour into shells. Refrigerate until set.

title: souper chicken
directions: Wash chicken well and pat dry.
Place chicken in a greased deep baking dish.
Add onions and celery over top of chicken.
Mix soups, milk, water, salt and pepper.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Mix dry stuffing mix and melted butter or margarine together and cover the top of the dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours until chicken is tender and topping is browned.

title: busy day casserole
directions: Crumble the beef into a 3-quart casserole and cook in microwave on full power 4 to 5 minutes or until beef is no longer pink, stirring halfway through cooking time.
Drain beef.
Mix in sauce, water and macaroni.
Cool, covered at full power 12 to 14 minutes, until macaroni is tender (you may have to add time if your microwave oven is less than 700 watts), stirring and rotating dish halfway through time.
Sprinkle cheese on top of casserole. Let stand, covered, 4 to 6 minutes before serving.
Yields 6 servings.

title: grammy's brownies
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt the chocolate in a medium saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat; stir in shortening, sugar and eggs until smooth.
In a small bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to chocolate mixture.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Bake for 25 minutes. Recipe can be doubled if a 9 x 13-inch pan is used.

title: oatmeal griddlecakes
directions: Heat milk to boil. Pour over oats. Let stand 10 minutes. Beat butter and egg. Combine dry ingredients. Stir until moistened. Add more milk if batter is too thick. Cook on hot griddle or skillet, browning on both sides.

title: butter pecan pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together except butter pecan icing.
Fold it in last. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Ice with bought caramel icing.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter light and fluffy.
Add sugar, beat good.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat.
Add syrup and vanilla, beat.
Add nuts.
Put tinfoil around edge of pie crust.
Bake at 300°.

title: jimmy carter cake
directions: Mix and pat into bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: john mazzeti
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Boil egg noodles.
Chop green pepper and onion.
When meat is brown and noodles are done, pour into large Dutch oven.
Set on medium high.
Add green pepper, onion, tomato juice and cream of mushroom soup.
When mixture is boiling, start slicing cheese and add to mixture.
When cheese has melted, it's ready to serve.
Great with salad and garlic bread.

title: turtle cake
directions: After preparing the cake mix, bake 1/2 of the batter at 325° for 10 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch well-greased pan.
Remove pan from oven.
Melt the caramels in the milk over low heat, stirring occasionally, or follow microwave instructions.
Pour the caramel-milk mixture over the cake in the pan.
Sprinkle the chocolate chips and pecans evenly over this.
Finally, spread the remainder of the cake batter over all.
Return to the oven; bake 30 minutes longer.
Let cool 20 minutes.
Ice in the pan.
Cut into squares in the pan.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: bonnie's whipped cream frosting
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and mix until light.

title: warm herb cheese spread
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat cheese just until smooth. Gradually beat in milk, then lemon juice.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 8 or 9-inch quiche dish or pie plate. Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until hot.
Serve warm with assorted crackers and/or vegetables.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: stew beef with mushroom gravy
directions: Overnight in a crock-pot, cook meat and onion.
Next day, stir in mushroom soup.
Serve over rice or creamed potatoes or cornbread and biscuits.

title: cheesy sausage bake
directions: Brown and drain sausage.
Grease a 9-inch square dish.
Unroll rolls and press evenly in bottom and 1 1/2 inches up sides of dish.
Spread sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour onto cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stove top shepherd's pie
directions: In a 10-inch skillet (safe to put in oven), cook meat, onion and chili powder over medium high heat until onion is tender and meat is cooked.
Stir in half the soup (undiluted), the water and pepper.
Bring to boil, reduce heat to low and simmer for 5 minutes.
Combine potatoes (already mashed), Cheddar cheese, green onion and remaining soup in medium bowl.
Spoon over meat in skillet, making mounds.
Cover skillet handle with foil to protect from heat.
Broil 6 inches from heat until potatoes begin to brown, about 3 minutes.

title: witches' brew(hot apple cider)
directions: Heat to boil, simmer 10 minutes.

title: connie's fruit salad
directions: Pour peaches with juice into 9x13 baking dish.
Add pineapple chunks (drain juice), strawberries, and banana slices.
Fruit can be cut to desired size.
Add Tang and vanilla pudding and mix thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator for several hours to enhance flavor.

title: zucchini relish(canning)
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and let stand overnight.
Wash in cold water and drain well.
Add peppers and 7 ingredients and cook 30 minutes over medium heat.
All together makes 7 to 8 pints.
Good over hot dogs and hamburgers.

title: potato soup
directions: In medium saucepan, saute onion and celery in margarine until tender.
Stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly until smooth and bubbly.
Gradually stir in chicken broth and milk; cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly. Do not boil.
Continue by adding crumbled bacon.

title: almond bark cookies
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a large bowl.
Melt almond bark over hot water.
Pour almond bark slowly over other ingredients. Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper to cool.
Makes about 80.

title: salad lilgeoise(warm potato salad)
directions: Cook beans in salted water.
They must remain firm.
Cook potatoes with skin in salt water.
Dice bacon and cook until crisp.
Peel potatoes and slice.
Drain beans and add to potatoes. Add parsley, onions, bacon and fat (as much as you like).
Pour vinegar in pan to loosen scrapings, reduce, add to salad.

title: fried won tons
directions: Heat oil in wok or frypan.
Place small amount of cream cheese on wrapper.
Fold and place in oil until lightly browned, about 1 minute.
Drain on paper towel.

title: chocolate bread pudding(century-old recipe)
directions: Stir cocoa into cold milk.
Add egg yolks and sugar.
Pour hot water over bread crumbs.
Add first mixture to bread crumbs, then stir in salt and vanilla.
Pour in buttered baking dish and set in pan of hot water.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove and cover with meringue made by folding the stiffly beaten egg whites with two teaspoons of sugar.
Put in oven and brown.

title: cranberry jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 1/2 cups boiling water.
Stir in cranberries, orange, celery, pineapple and sugar.
Refrigerate. This is a pretty, crispy salad.

title: cream potato soup
directions: Cover potatoes, celery and onion with water in saucepan. Salt and pepper and cook until done.
Drain about 2/3 of the water off. Cover with milk.
Add a chunk of butter; salt and pepper again to taste.
Bring to a boil.
Thicken to desired consistency with flour thickening.
May add cheese if you want.

title: cube steaks with gravy(crock-pot)
directions: Place flour in large resealable plastic bag. Add the steaks, a few at a time, and shake until completely coated. In a skillet, fry the steaks in oil until lightly browned on each side. Transfer to slow cooker. Add onion and 2 cups water. Cover and cook on low 8 hours or until meat is tender.

title: ernie's marinated flank steak
directions: Pierce steak with a fork and place in shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients, mixing well.
Pour over steak.
Let stand at room temperature for 3 to 4 hours.
Remove steak from marinade and place on a lightly greased broiler pan.
Broil 6 inches from heat, 4 to 5 minutes on each side.
Slice across the grain in thin slices for best results.
Delicious over noodles or rice!

title: chicken breast surprise
directions: Mix soups, milk and rice together in bowl.
Place in shallow greased 2-quart baking dish.
Arrange chicken breasts, skin side up on rice mixture.
Sprinkle with onion soup.
Cover.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: delicious fish
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together in a small bowl and set aside. Place fish in a single layer in a lightly greased pan. Pour lemon juice over and sprinkle with pepper. Broil 6 to 10 minutes or until fish flakes with a fork. Remove from oven. Spread with cheese mixture. Return to broiler for an additional 2 to 3 minutes or until cheese is lightly browned and bubbly. Serves 6.

title: hedwig's red cabbage
directions: In a large enameled or heavy pan, bring the water and vinegar to a boil with sugar, spices and herbs.
Add the apple and cabbage and return to a boil.
Cover and reduce the heat.
Simmer on low heat, stirring occasionally, until the cabbage is tender, but not too soft.
Remove bay leaf and clove.
(Check for tenderness after 20 minutes.)
Stir in a tablespoon of butter just before serving, if desired.

title: quick oatmeal cookies
directions: Work all ingredients together with fingers until blended. Press into small balls on a cookie sheet.
Flatten each one with a moistened fork, dipping the fork in water each time to prevent sticking.
Bake about 15 minutes or until lightly browned in a 350 degree oven.
Let cool on cookie sheet for a minute or two then remove with spatula.

title: corn bread
directions: Beat together egg, buttermilk and honey.
Mix well together all dry ingredients.
Combine all ingredients, including melted butter and mix well.
Pour into a greased 8-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.
You can also make muffins!

title: green tomato mincemeat
directions: Sprinkle chopped tomatoes with salt; let stand for 1 hour. Drain.
Cover tomatoes with boiling water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Add grated rind and pulp of orange.
Mix together the remaining ingredients; cook until mixture is thick. Pack into sterilized jars and seal.
This is a delicious treat, and I know you will love it.

title: banana crush
directions: To Freeze:
Dissolve sugar in water.
Add juices.
Peel and mash bananas.
Put through food mill.
Stir in juice.
Ladle into wide top freezer containers, leaving 1-inch head space.
Cover tightly and freeze.

title: chocolate truffles
directions: Cook brownie mix as directed.
Punch holes in hot brownies. Pour Kahlua on top and cool.
Take 1/3 crumbled brownies and put in glass bowl.
Add 1/3 pudding mix, 1/3 Cool Whip and 1/3 crumbled Heath bars.
Layer 3 times.
Refrigerate.

title: dark night barbecue sauce
directions: Add all ingredients to pan and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Coat chopped, cooked pork roast with sauce and place on hamburger buns with lettuce, sliced onion and tomato slices.
Ingredients may be doubled or cut in half, if more or less sauce is needed.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and 1 cup cheese into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan or dish.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine in casserole.
Put 1 can peas in bottom, 1/2 of mushroom soup.
Pour other can in casserole and put the other half on top.
Cook until it bubbles and add onion. Brown onions.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together, then add pineapple, bananas, nuts, eggs, vanilla and oil.
Then after mixed thoroughly, pour into 3 greased and floured cake pans.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: delicious cucumbers
directions: Peel and slice cucumbers; cover with salt water for 1 hour. Rinse and dry.
Mix vinegar and mayonnaise; pour over cucumbers. Cover; refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: ranch-style baked beans
directions: Saut onion with sausage and then combine with remaining ingredients. Bake for 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: shrimp, artichoke and pasta salad
directions: Use artichoke water and enough more water to cover shrimp to boil; add heavy seasoning of salt and lemon juice or crab boil. Retain water; drain shrimp.
Boil pasta in shrimp water.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash
and onions together; drain off water.
Mix with eggs,
cheese,
salt,
pepper and crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown and drain the hamburger.
Add the remaining ingredients. Less noodles and more green peppers may be added.
No salt since soup and noodles are salted.
Place into a lightly greased medium casserole.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy pastry
directions: Melt oleo in pie pan. Add flour and sugar. Mix and press over pie plate and up sides. Bake at 400° about 10 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Roll in pecans and keep chilled until ready to serve.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to directions on package.
Drain and put in casserole dish.
Slice cheese in thick slices and cover the top.
Crush crackers and cover top.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly.

title: party chicken
directions: Wrap each chicken breast in a strip of bacon.
Place the package of chipped beef in the bottom of a baking dish.
Lay wrapped chicken breasts on top of the chipped beef.
Cover with a mixture of the soup and sour cream.
Bake in a 325° oven until tender.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large mixing bowl; mix.
Pour into 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until a fork, when poked in center, comes out clean.
Cool at least 2 hours.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir in milk and vanilla.
Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart onto greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Steam or stir-fry broccoli.
Make a sauce of water, vinegar, soy sauce, cornstarch, sugar and seasonings and add pineapple, chicken and broccoli.
Heat and serve over chow mein noodles or cooked rice.
Serves 8.

title: brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar. Mix in eggs. Mix in syrup. Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix. Add vanilla and nuts. Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Yield: 3 dozen.

title: ruby scott's famous turkey salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
Chill in the refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.
Serve.

title: johnny cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake 25 minutes at 425° in a square pan.

title: martha washington's fudge frosting
directions: Combine sugar, water, syrup and salt in a saucepan.
Bring quickly to a boil, stirring only until sugar is dissolved.
Then boil until a little forms a very soft ball in cold water.
Remove from fire and cool to lukewarm (110°) without stirring.
Melt chocolate over boiling water; add butter.
Add syrup gradually and mix well.
Continue stirring until smooth and, if it gets too hard, place over boiling water and stir until of the right consistency to spread.
Add vanilla after the syrup has been added.

title: stuffed eggplant
directions: Cut each eggplant into 2 equal parts; remove middle and chop up.
Add onions, celery, oleo and garlic.
Smother until done. Put buns and eggs into a bowl to soak.
When buns are completely soaked, mix well with chopped, boiled shrimp, smothered eggplant, crab meat and green onions.
Season to taste.
Boil shells of the eggplant for 10 minutes or until tender, then stuff them with mixture.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: four bean salad
directions: Place beans, green pepper and onion in a large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients; drizzle over vegetables.
Cover; marinate for several hours or overnight, stirring once or twice.
Before serving, stir and drain.
Flavor improves as it stands.
Yields 12 servings.

title: fried peach pies
directions: Mix and chill at least 1 hour.
Roll out dough; cut into 3-inch rounds.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 45 minutes at 350° in greased loaf pan.
Makes 2 small loaves or 1 large loaf.

title: church supper potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease bottom and sides of a 13 x 9 x 3-inch baking dish and rub with the garlic clove.
Thinly slice potatoes and quickly place in large bowl of ice water.
In a cup, mix the flour, salt and pepper.
Drain the potatoes and arrange 1/2 of them in the dish.
Top with onions, flour mixture, bacon and the remaining potatoes.
Brush with the butter, then pour milk over all.
Cover and bake 45 minutes.
Uncover and bake 15 minutes more or until tender.

title: 15 layer cake with iron skillet chocolate icing
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and creamy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time, mixing thoroughly.
Stir together flour and cake mix.
With mixer at low speed, alternately add dry ingredients, milk and sour cream to butter mix.
Mix well.
Use cooking spray before adding 3/4 cup batter to each pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool and frost.

title: ham biscuits
directions: Melt margarine and put in onions and mustard.
Blend.
Spread sauce on bottom of layer of rolls.
Then place ham slices and put cheese slices on top.
Place roll tops over layer.
Bake 15 minutes at 350° in tinfoil.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix all together and make balls.
Roll in flour and brown in skillet.
Grease a casserole or put in Dutch oven.
Cover with sauce.

title: stir-fried okra
directions: Stir-fry the first 7 ingredients for 6 to 10 minutes.
Add tomatoes and stir-fry 2 more minutes.
Sprinkle with soy sauce.

title: fried muskrat
directions: Cut the muskrat into serving size pieces and soak in salted water overnight.
Place the meat in a pot, add 1 quart of water, salt, pepper, garlic powder and onion.
Cook about 1 hour.
Brown meat in vegetable oil.
Pour ketchup seasoned with 1 teaspoon garlic powder over the meat.
Add some water and simmer about 30 minutes.

title: monster cookies
directions: In a large bowl, mix the ingredients in order given.
Use 1/4 cup measuring cup to shape the cookies on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix water and yeast; mix sugar and butter.
Combine all ingredients.
Put
into
airtight bowl in refrigerator.
Dough is better when good and cold or made the night before.
Grease muffin pan;
spoon
tablespoons of dough.
Bake at 350° until done.
Use large enough container for rising.

title: bisquick cheddar garlic biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450 degrees.
Mix bisquick, milk, and cheese to form a soft dough.
Drop 9 spoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 8-10 minutes.
Mix butter and garlic powder; brush over warm biscuits.

title: holiday candy
directions: Spread over a 6 x 8-inch pan.
Melt butter in heavy pan.
Add brown sugar until candy thermometer reaches 268° to 270° (hard ball stage).
Put nuts on pan.
Pour hot mixture over nuts.
Place Hershey bars on top of hot mixture.
Let melt and spread over top. Refrigerate until hard.
Break in pieces.
Store in refrigerator. Yummy.

title: rice casserole
directions: In large deep casserole dish, mix together first 4 ingredients.
Slice margarine on top.
Bake 50 minutes at 400° uncovered.
Stir every 15 minutes!

title: pina colada cake
directions: Drain
pineapple
well.
Reserve
liquid.
Prepare cake mix according
to
directions on package, using the pineapple juice instead of water.
Add more water to equal liquid amount directed on
cake mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan according to package directions.
When
cool,
frost with mixed pineapple, Cool Whip and coconut.
Refrigerate until serving.

title: lemon cake
directions: Place all fruit in bowl.
Mix 1 cup flour with fruit.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add Karo and lemon extract.
Alternate flour and eggs.
Beat well.
Pour mixture over fruit and nuts.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
Double recipe makes 5 loaves.

title: midwest chowder
directions: Combine vegetables with boiling water.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes (until tender).
Make cream sauce of margarine, flour and milk.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add vegetables.
Add corn; heat to serve.
Do not boil after adding vegetables.

title: cheesy beef dip
directions: Brown ground beef with onion; add tomatoes.
Simmer and drain. Add cheese and taco sauce to beef mixture.
Cook until cheese melts.
Serve in crock-pot on low.

title: pasta fagioli
directions: Combine oil, onions, bacon and garlic and saut.
Add chicken broth and tomatoes.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; add beans, cheese and spices.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Add cooked pasta.

title: mounds bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and bake 10 minutes.
Mix coconut and Eagle brand milk. Put over top and bake 10 to 15 minutes.
Melt chocolate chips and peanut butter.
Melt and spread over top.

title: zucchini tomato salad
directions: Cook zucchini in small amount of water until very crisp. Drain and cool.
Place in a small bowl and sprinkle with dressing, oregano, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Marinate for an hour. Before serving, arrange zucchini on a salad plate, surrounded by tomato wedges and topped with green onion.

title: swiss pot roast
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; coat both sides of roast. Brown in hot Crisco in a heavy kettle.
Add all ingredients. Cover.
Simmer over low heat or until tender.
Makes 6 servings.

title: waffles
directions: Combine eggs, oil and milk in electric mixer bowl; mix well. Combine dry ingredients; add to egg mixture, beating at medium speed.
Beat for about 2 minutes.
Pour batter into hot waffle iron.
Bake until done.
Serve with favorite topping.
Yields 6 servings.

title: wayne's poor man pudding
directions: Boil potatoes for 15 minutes.
Put sliced potatoes in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix soup and brown gravy mix together.
Pour over potatoes.
Mix ground beef and onion together.
Make balls (about 2-inches) and place on top of casserole.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy cobbler
directions: Spray the casserole dish with cooking spray. Pour pie filling in casserole dish (medium). Put dry cake mix over this, then slice the oleo thinly and completely cover the cake mix. Fill any uncovered spaces with squeeze oleo. Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.

title: sausage bake
directions: Brown onion and sausage in skillet.
Add rest of ingredients in casserole dish.
Cook in oven at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: brie wheel with phyllo
directions: Cover Brie with several layers of phyllo.
Keep tightly covered with
waxed
paper	until
time to cook.
In preheated oven at 350°, place Brie onto a pizza-type pan and cook for 15 minutes.
Remove
from
oven
(leave in pan), top with apricot preserves,	then
with almonds.
Place crackers or gingersnaps on pan around the Brie and serve hot.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar, eggs, butter and vanilla, then add chips and pecans.
Put in pie shell and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: edna's roll recipe
directions: Mix potatoes and Crisco.
Add eggs, sugar and yeast, then add 3 cups sifted flour.
Can be kept in refrigerator several days.

title: 7-up pound cake
directions: Cream well the butter, Crisco, sugar and eggs.
Add the 7-Up and flour.
Add extract.
Bake in tube pan lined with waxed paper and greased for about 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°.

title: easy scampi
directions: Peel raw fresh shrimp; put in a baking pan.
Add butter, garlic, lemon juice and oregano.
Broil until shrimp is pink (15 minutes).
Serve with rice pilaf.
Serves 4.

title: christmas holly cookies
directions: Melt marshmallows with margarine.
Add vanilla, food coloring and corn flakes.
Mix well.
Drop onto wax paper.
Place 3 cinnamon candies for berries.

title: chocolate chip pie(serve warm with ice cream.)
directions: Mix by hand flour and sugar; add other ingredients, stir in chips; put in unbaked pie shell and cook 300° 45-55 minutes.

title: babe ruth bars
directions: Boil the first 3 ingredients together 1 minute.
Add and stir peanut butter.
Pour over cereal and nuts.
Pat into buttered cookie sheet and score in desired size pieces.

title: tortillas and fish
directions: In
a large skillet, saute the	green
onions,	pepper, celery and spinach or bok choy; set aside
to
cool.
Pan-fry fish
in small amount of butter.
Cool and
shred
the
fish. Combine the vegies and flavor with salt and pepper.
Heat corn or flour tortillas.	Roll in vegies and fish.
May
be
served warm or cold.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef, sausage (out of casing) and onion.
Grate Mozzarella cheese; put aside.
Cook noodles until tender.
Mix parsley, Ricotta and egg together; set aside.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Cool and add strawberries and drained pineapple.
Chill until mixture starts to thicken.

title: cauliflower-crab meat casserole
directions: Separate cauliflower into flowerets; boil until tender.
Drain and place in greased casserole dish.
Remove shell tissue from crab meat; flake and add celery soup and milk.
Pour crab meat mixture over cauliflower.
Top with grated cheese; sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until browned.

title: chop suey
directions: Dredge meat with flour.
Brown meat in large Teflon pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Simmer for 1 hour or until meat is tender.
Serve with cooked rice.
Serves 4.

title: dried beef cheese dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with sour cream and milk.
Add other ingredients.
Top with pecan pieces sauteed in margarine.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: raspberry mold
directions: Heat applesauce until it bubbles.
Add package of jello (no water) and stir until dissolved.
Add raspberries, including syrup.
Pour into 3 1/2 cup mold and refrigerate until set.
Can easily be doubled or tripled.
Can also be made sugar-free by using D-Zerta and frozen raspberries with no sugar added.
When serving, sour cream or small curd cottage cheese can be used in center if ring mold is used.

title: maple country pork ribs
directions: Place ribs in a large Dutch oven. Cover with water; bring to a boil. Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes. Drain and place ribs in a greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan. Combine remaining ingredients; pour half over the ribs. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender, basting often with the remaining sauce.

title: turkey-cheddar muffins
directions: Carefully separate each biscuit into 4 thin layers of dough. Spray 8 cups of a 12-cup muffin pan with nonstick cooking spray; place 1 layer of dough in bottom of each sprayed cup.
Set aside.

title: italian peas
directions: Place frozen peas in a greased 11 x 13-inch pan.
Layer with mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Melt butter.
Pour over layers. Sprinkle with dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stuffed shrimp with italian ham
directions: In a bowl, mix bread crumbs, garlic, parsley, oregano, cheese, Prosciutto, olive oil and salt.
Do not remove shells or tails from shrimp.
Devein, wash and drain.
Make a slit in shrimp deep enough for it to lie flat, shell sides down.
Fill each with stuffing.
On bottom of 14-inch round baking pan, pour 1 cup cold water or enough to coat it.
Place shrimp in pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 25 minutes or until tender.
Serves 3.

title: chocolate pie
directions: *Cool Whip may be used instead of whipping cream.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Put rice in a baking dish.
Place chicken pieces on it.
Mix water, mushroom soup and onion soup mix together.
Pour over the chicken and rice. Cover dish.
Place in a 400° oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fire alarm chili
directions: Melt the margarine in a large skillet.
Crumble and brown ground beef, adding salt and pepper to taste.
Skim off excess fat.
Add Worcestershire sauce, chili powder, sugar and onions and continue cooking until onions are almost done.
Chop the tomatoes and add them along with the beans.
Bring the mixture to a boil and simmer for about one hour.

title: green bean soup
directions: Place ham bone in soup kettle with water to cover.
Tie allspice, parsley and savory in small cheesecloth bag or put in tea ball.
Add to kettle.
Simmer 2 hours, adding more water if needed.
Add potatoes, onion and beans.
Cook until vegetables are tender, 20 to 30 minutes.
Remove spice ball.
Just before serving, blend in cream, butter and salt.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in skins until done.
Cool and slice thin (not cold).
Fry bacon in a large frying pan.
After it is crisp, add half of the bacon to the potatoes.
Add 1/2 of the chopped onion to the bacon grease; cook until tender, then add flour slowly to the bacon grease (otherwise it will scorch).
Let it cook slowly for 8 minutes; combine the vinegar and water, then add the vinegar mixture slowly.
Add the sugar, salt and dash of pepper.
Add the other half of the onion to the potatoes before you add the bacon mixture.
Pour the mixture over the potatoes and toss the potatoes lightly (so they do not break up).
Put in chopped eggs and sugar if needed.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
If mixture is too thick, add a little cold water to the vinegar from the frying pan; heat and add to the potatoes.

title: venetian rice and peas
directions: Saute bacon in frying pan.
Remove bacon and grease.
Saute onion in butter; add frozen peas.
Cook 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add rice and cook until well coated with butter. Pour in chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer.
Stir occasionally for 20 minutes or until liquid is absorbed.
Toss with crumbled bacon and Parmesan cheese.

title: sweet-sour coleslaw
directions: Combine cabbage, bell pepper and onion in a large bowl.
Bring sugar, vinegar, salt, mustard, celery seed and oil to boil until sugar dissolves.
Pour over cabbage and refrigerate overnight.

title: blueberry cake roll
directions: Put in pan; cook until thick.
Chill in refrigerator.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: Boil and debone chicken. Arrange half the uncooked broccoli in casserole dish. Put layer of chicken. Pour half mixture over broccoli and chicken. Repeat layers using remaining ingredients. Top with buttered Ritz crackers (3/4 package Ritz crackers and 3/4 to 1 stick melted margarine). Bake 30 to 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: bacon baked beans
directions: Fry the bacon until crispy.
Remove and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Add onion, green pepper and celery to drippings.
Simmer for 5 to 6 minutes or until tender.
Drain off grease.
Add bacon and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: roquefort log
directions: Combine cheeses.
Blend in next 4 ingredients.
Chill.
Shape a roll 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Coat with nuts.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Refrigerate until firm.
Slice and serve with bacon flavored crackers.
Makes about 1 cup spread.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook and drain spinach; add remaining ingredients.
Top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix together.
Make balls and brown in skillet.
Put meatballs in crock-pot and cover with mushroom gravy sauce (several cans). Cook on low 3 to 4 hours (gravy and balls).

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Grease heated griddle with shortening.
For each pancake, pour about 1/4 cup of batter onto the hot griddle.
Cook until pancakes are puffed and dry around edges.
Turn and cook on other side until golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 pancakes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans in own juice about 15 minutes; drain.
Add 1/2 can milk to soup and mix well; then add water chestnuts.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 375° until hot, about 25 minutes. About 5 minutes before done, sprinkle onions on top and cook until browned.

title: prune nut cupcakes
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and eggs.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add prunes, raisins and nuts.
Fill cupcake paper lined pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: "it's the batter that matters" fried chicken
directions: In bowl, mix first five ingredients.
Add water and egg.
Stir until smooth.
Fill large skillet half full of oil.
Heat over medium heat until about 375°.
Dip chicken into batter, a few cubes at a time.
Carefully add to hot oil.
Cook 2 - 3 minutes, turning once until golden brown and crisp.
Drain on paper towel.

title: mamaw's banana pudding
directions: Beat eggs, sugar and cornstarch together.
Then add Pet milk and 2% milk.
Cook over low heat for 10 minutes until thick. Remove from heat.
In a casserole dish layer wafers, bananas and filling.
Repeat until you have used up all of the filling and bananas.

title: skillet enchiladas
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, brown ground beef and onion; drain off excess fat (electric skillet at 350°).
Stir in soup, enchilada sauce, milk and chilies.
Reduce heat (220°), cover and cook 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: sweet 'n sour shrimp
directions: In medium size skillet, heat 1 1/2 to 2 inches oil to 375°. Meanwhile, blend eggs with flour for batter.
Add shrimp and toss to coat evenly.
Fry in salad oil until golden on all sides. Remove to heated platter.
Pour off all but 2 tablespoons oil. Saute green pepper just until transparent, but not limp.
Add pineapple with juice, vinegar, sugar, cornstarch paste, salt and soy sauce.
Cook 6 to 7 minutes, stirring constantly.
Stir in shrimp.
Serve over rice.
Makes about 5 to 6 servings.

title: triple chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan with fork, scraping corners frequently, until it's moist.
Stir batter vigorously with fork for 1 minute.
Scrape sides with rubber spatula.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until top springs back when lightly touched.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: aunt ruth's coffee drop cookies
directions: Mix and cream first four ingredients.
Combine flour, salt, soda, baking powder and spices; sift together until thoroughly mixed.
Alternately combine flour and coffee and stir after each addition.
Add raisins last and stir thoroughly.
Drop by tablespoons on greased cookie sheets about 1 1/2 inches part. Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 325° to 350°.
Yields 62 to 65 cookies.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook
macaroni	as directed.
Melt 4 tablespoons butter and stir
in
flour.
Cook
until
bubbly.
Add
mustard
and Worcestershire sauce
and
bring
milk to a boil with onion in it. Strain
into flour mixture and stir.
Add cheese and stir again. Put
macaroni into a buttered casserole and pour sauce over it. Melt
remaining
butter and mix in crumbs.	Sprinkle over top and bake 30 minutes in a 375° oven.
"Yummy".

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in greased loaf pan. Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: fig oat drop cookies
directions: Make potatoes as directed on package; sift dry ingredients. Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, molasses and mashed potatoes. Mix together fruits, nuts and oats and add alternately with dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: lefse(norwegian flat bread)
directions: Let riced potatoes cool well, then add the other ingredients. Roll out thin and fry on pancake griddle with no oils applied. Serve with butter and sugar for a good snack.
May also use as a crepe with fruit, jelly or egg, rolled up.

title: magic genie dessert
directions: Spread one graham cracker square lightly with cream cheese. Top with All Fruit spread, your favorite flavor (strawberry, apricot, raspberry or peach).
This makes a delightful, quick, low-fat, low-sugar dessert; especially nice for people with sugar diabetes.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in butter until crisp, but not tender.
Cream sour cream with eggs, salt, pepper and cayenne.
Mix with onions and pour into crust.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake another 20 minutes, until brown.

title: poor man's steak soup
directions: Brown.
Drain ground beef.
In large pot, combine all ingredients except flour/cornstarch.
Cook until vegetables are done.
Thicken to desired consistency.

title: indian chicken
directions: In food processor or blender, combine all ingredients, except chicken, until smooth.
Pound cutlets 1/4-inch thick between 2 sheets of wax paper.
Place chicken and marinade in large Ziploc bag and marinate in refrigerator overnight, turning once.
Preheat broiler.
Place chicken on broiler pan, brush with marinade. Broil 4-inches from heat 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fried cheese sandwich
directions: Spread 1 slice bread with mayonnaise.
Top with cheese. Butter remaining bread slice.
Place, unbuttered-side down, on cheese.
Melt pat of butter in skillet.
Place sandwich, unbuttered-side down, in skillet.
Cook until brown and cheese melts.
Turn sandwich over and brown.
Yield: 1 serving.

title: stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Rub potatoes with oil.
Pierce with fork.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 20 minutes or until tender.
Allow potatoes to cool to the touch.

title: thanksgiving pie
directions: Butter a 10-inch pie pan or 2 small ones.
Put cranberries, walnuts and 1/2 cup of sugar in pie pan and mix.

title: kitchen floor pickles
directions: Use small to medium sized cucumbers.
Pack tightly in a gallon jar.
